            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Course Description</p><p>The purpose of this course is to familiarize the students with the cognitive bases of behavior. The course will review and cover topics like perception, attention, learning, memory, language, problem-solving, reasoning, and thinking. These are the core cognitive processes and are involved in making sense of the environment and interacting with it. The cognitive processes like perception, attention, learning, memory, language, problem solving, reasoning, and thinking will be studied using experimental methods and findings. Empirical studies will be critically reviewed to understand cognitive processes.</p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>At the end of the course, students should be able to:</p><p>1. Understand and critically evaluate theory and research in Cognitive Psycholgy</p><p>2. Understand basic research methods will have conceptual expertise in evaluation cognitive research methods</p><p>3. Demonstrate the ability to read, analyze, summarize, present scientific literature, and generate meaningful questions;</p><p>4. Explain how theories and research findings from cognitive psychology can inform everyday problems</p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Solso, R. L., Maclin O.H., Maclin M.K., (2014) Cognitive Psychology, 8th Edition. Essex, UK. Pearson</p><p>Anderson, J. R. (2005). Cognitive psychology and its implications. Macmillan.</p><p>Goldstein, E.B. (2018). Cognitive Psychology: Connecting Mind, Research, and Everyday Experience. Cengage (5th Edition)</p><p>Eysenck, M. W., &amp; Keane, M. T. (2020). Cognitive Psychology: A Student's Handbook (8th edition).</p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Evaluation*</p><p>Student presentation: 15%</p><p>Class participation &amp; Discussion: 10%</p><p>Assignment 1 - 20%</p><p>Assignment 2 - 20%</p><p>Weekly Quizzes - 10%</p><p>Take Home Exam: 20%</p><p>Attendance : 0.5% per week, up to a maximum of 5%.</p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>There will be no distinction between absences due to temporary illnesses, willful truancy, or misplaced priorities. If you have chronic medical conditions, please talk to your instructor.</p></div></div>",
