            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><pre>U.F.D. , P.I.D, Euclidean domains. Field extensions.   Normal extensions, Separable extensions.  Detailed study of finite fields.Galois extensions, Galois group. Fundamental theorem of Galois theory.Cyclic Extensions, Solvability by radicals.   Geometric constructions.  Transcendental extensions.   Solvable and nilpotent groups.   Fundamental theorem for Abelian groups.  Presentation of groups.   Semi-direct products, amalgamated products and HNN- extensions. </pre></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Requirements: Algebra 1, Linear Algebra.</p><p> </p><p>Textbooks: </p><ol dir=\"ltr\"><li>Michael Artin: Algebra, Second Edition, Pearson Prentice-Hall of India, New Delhi, 2011.</li><li>David S. Dummit and Richard M. Foote: Abstract Algebra, Third Edition, Wiley, 2005.</li><li><i>Field and Galois Theory</i> by Patrick Morandi. Springer, 1996.</li></ol> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Quiz 20%</p><p>Assignments 25 %</p><p>Midsem 25 %</p><p>Final 30 %</p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Not mandatory but strongly encouraged. </p></div></div>",
