            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>This course provides an introduction to modern cryptography and its applications to network security. It is divided into two parts. The first part is the main part where we provide an introduction to modern cryptography, which focuses on the classical goals of cryptography, such as data privacy, authenticity, and integrity. We cover the fundamentals of symmetric-key cryptography and public-key cryptography. In the second part we study some prominent Internet security protocols in which various cryptographic algorithms are used. The main topics include: </p><p>Cryptography </p><p>- Symmetric-key Encryption, Hash Function, Message Authentication Code, Key Agreement, Public-key Encryption, Digital Signature  </p><p>Network Security </p><p>Public-key Infrastructure, Key Distribution, and User Authentication, Application-layer Security (HTTPS, DNSSec), Transport-layer Security (TLS), IP Security (IPSec), Electronic Mail Security (PGP, S/MIME), Wireless Network Security (WEP/WPA)</p><p> </p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Please see the attachment</p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Please see the attachment</p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Not Applicable </p><p>Please see the attachment</p></div></div><div><strong>Attachment</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><table><tbody><tr><td><a style=\"color:blue\" href=\"https://ams.ashoka.edu.in/UploadFiles/CourseCatalogueFiles/55f20ee9-d4e4-4b25-a6e1-d3dbd279d472.pdf\" download=\"CS2362_Spring22_CourseOverview.pdf\">CS2362_Spring22_CourseOverview.pdf</a></td></tr></tbody></table></div></div>",
