            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>To understand the theory of Fourier series and transform and their<br>uses.  The definition of the series and transform, the<br>convergence of the series and transform, the kind of functions that can be represented<br>by the them will be covered.  In the process various notions of convergence<br>will be learnt.  Some uses of the series and transform will be covered.  Fast and Discrete Fourier transforms will be introduced. </p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Understanding Fourier Series and Transform and how to use them.</p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Text Book </p><p>Elias M. Stein, Rami Shakarchi,  <strong>Fourier Analysis -  An Introduction</strong>,  Princeton University Press</p><p>Additional Reading</p><p>Rajendra Bhatia,  <strong>Fourier Series</strong>,  Hindustan Book Agency (2003).</p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Will be announced in Class</p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Will be announced in Class</p></div></div>",
