            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 8pt; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Instructor: Prof. Anshu Ogra. This introductory course aims to help students gain an interdisciplinary understanding of environmental issues.  It will highlight how environmental challenges are deeply embedded in the social, political, and economic context in which they are experienced. It will show how the interdisciplinary nature of environmental problems such as pollution and climate change requires a holistic understanding. The conceptual framing of the course will use perspectives from science and technology studies (STS).</span></span></p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>TBA</p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>TBA</p></div></div>",
