            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\" lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">This course will be an introduction into the economic way of thinking about the world and of analyzing questions and figuring out answers. It will cover both Microeconomics and Macroeconomics and lay the foundation for the methodology and practices in both. It will aim to equip students with basic comprehension of demand, supply, markets, the economic basis for trade, national income accounting, prices and inflation, real and nominal measures of GDP; and help students understand externalities and welfare, the choices in the labor market and its resulting level of employment, and the role of government in markets and the economy. Additional topics in Micro &amp; Macro economics might be covered depending on the pace of the course. </span></span></span></p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Course material will use recommended textbooks and excerpts from journal articles, news and other media, and other sources. The recommended textbooks are:</span></span></span></p><ol><li style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">The Economy, by The CORE project/team: <a href=\"https://www.core-econ.org/project/core-the-economy/\" style=\"color:#0563c1; text-decoration:underline\">https://www.core-econ.org/project/core-the-economy/</a> </span></span></span></li><li style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 8pt 36pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">The Economy: A South Asian Perspective, by The CORE project/team: <a href=\"https://www.core-econ.org/project/the-economy-a-south-asian-perspective/\" style=\"color:#0563c1; text-decoration:underline\">https://www.core-econ.org/project/the-economy-a-south-asian-perspective/</a> </span></span></span></li></ol><p><em><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\" lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Some material will also use the textbook, Economics, by Acemoglu, Laibson &amp; List (2016), Global Edition, Pearson Education.</span></span></span></em></p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\" lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">25% of course grade on class participation; 35% on quizzes/assignments spaced out through the semester; and 40% on a final exam. </span></span></span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\" lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Attendance is important for this course. There will be short quizzes in class without any pre-announcement. Students will be graded on their responses in these quizzes, either individually or in groups, as well as on attendance taken randomly in class. Together these will be considered as the students\u2019 performance on \u2018class participation\u2019. </span></span></span></p></div></div>",
