            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"background:#fcfdfd\"><span style=\"line-height:15.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Corbel&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#c00000\">COURSE OVERVIEW</span></span></span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom:0cm; text-align:center; margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\" align=\"center\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><i><span style=\"background:white\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Corbel&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:maroon\">For a biologist, the alternative to thinking in evolutionary terms is not to think at all.<br>\u2014 Peter B. Medawar (Nobel Laureate, 1960)</span></span></span></i></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom:0cm; text-align:justify; margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"> </p><p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"background:#fcfdfd\"><span style=\"line-height:15.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Corbel&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">This is a basic introductory course for students who want to learn how modern biology started its journey in the mid-19th century and continues to mature till date. I will begin by discussing the grandeur of evolution, arguably the greatest show of the living world, and how it is irreversibly intertwined with genetics. Using historical contexts, I will introduce key debates in Genetics and Evolution that shrugged the initial days of Modern Biological Synthesis and then gradually move into advanced concepts of Evolutionary theory and Mendelian Genetics that will lay the foundation of the Biology curriculum at Ashoka. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\">A tentative course structure is attached</p><p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"> </p><p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><b><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Corbel&quot;,sans-serif\">Course instructor:</span></b> </span></span></span></p><p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Corbel&quot;,sans-serif\">Imroze Khan, Assistant Professor of Biology &amp; DBT-Wellcome Trust Intermediate Fellow </span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><i><span style=\"background:white\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Corbel&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">\u201cI am an evolutionary geneticist who is broadly interested in understanding how immune system can evolve under infection, disease and climate warming, using tools as varied as experimental evolution, genetics and genomics\u201d</span></span></span></i></span></span></span></p><p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><i><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Corbel&quot;,sans-serif\">Webpage: </span></i><a href=\"https://myevoecoimmunol.com/\" style=\"color:#0563c1; text-decoration:underline\"><i><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Corbel&quot;,sans-serif\">https://myevoecoimmunol.com/</span></i></a></span></span></span></p><p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><i><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Corbel&quot;,sans-serif\">E- </span></i><a href=\"mailto:imroze.khan@ashoka.edu.in\" style=\"color:#0563c1; text-decoration:underline\"><i><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Corbel&quot;,sans-serif\">imroze.khan@ashoka.edu.in</span></i></a></span></span></span></p><p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><i><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Corbel&quot;,sans-serif\">On Twitter- </span></i><a href=\"https://twitter.com/evoimmunoimroze\" style=\"color:#0563c1; text-decoration:underline\" title=\"\u200e@evoimmunoimroze on Twitter\"><i><span style=\"background:white\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Corbel&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#2b7bb9\">@evoimmunoimroze</span></span></span></i></a></span></span></span></p><p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"> </p><p style=\"margin-bottom:7.5pt; text-align:justify; margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><br> </p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin-bottom:7.5pt; text-align:justify; margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"background:#fcfdfd\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Corbel&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#c5122f\">LEARNING OUTCOMES</span></span></span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"background:#fcfdfd\"><span style=\"line-height:15.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Corbel&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">This course primarily aims to strengthen the philosophy of studying Biology where understanding concepts and the ability to synthesize ideas are more important than mere acquisition of mundane information. At the end of the course, students will not only be familiar with the key concepts of Evolutionary Processes and genetics, but also understand how they can collectively contribute to the development of almost other areas of modern biology, including our current research efforts on climate change, antibiotic-drug resistance and emerging infectious diseases such as SARS, MERS and COVID-19.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>TBA</p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>TBA</p></div></div><div><strong>Attachment</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><table><tbody><tr><td><a style=\"color:blue\" href=\"https://ams.ashoka.edu.in/UploadFiles/CourseCatalogueFiles/2243861b-e0f6-47f1-a72d-08197ef6d3b5.pdf\" download=\"Course structure.pdf\">Course structure.pdf</a></td></tr></tbody></table></div></div>",
