            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12px;\">Imagine a very nice evening, a group of close friends with their guitar, violin etc. getting bonfire at beach. This is what one can wish for a perfect evening -- water waves hitting the shore, a pleasant sound of music and of course the warmth of fire. But hold on! What it all has to do with this class? And here comes, you see, what you want to see! </span></span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12px;\">What is common in this all is \u2013 WAVES \u2013 some times visible in the form of water waves, but not so apparent in the other forms, of sound and light! And what these waves actually are? They are correlated collection of \u201cOSCILLATIONS\u201d. The oscillations play a vital role in Physics, be it classical or quantum, and it is widely accepted that \u201cthe domain of physics is all phenomena that can be reduced to coupled oscillators\u201d.</span></span></p><p> </p><p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12px;\"><b style=\"\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Contents*:</span></b></span></span></p><p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0cm 0cm 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12px;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Simple harmonic oscillation, damped and force oscillation, coupled oscillations, oscillation of a string, Sound waves, superposition of waves Electromagnetic waves, <span style=\"color:#424242\">Fresnel\u2019s laws of </span>reflection and refraction, interference, diffraction, Laser.</span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0.0001pt\"> </p><p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12px;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">*Details will be added further!</span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Cambria\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Open Sans&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\"><span style=\"color:#333333\"> </span></span></span></span></span></span></p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0cm 0cm 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12px;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">In this course, Oscillation, Wave and Optics, </span><span style=\"background:white\">we will study a number of underlying principles and will see that the wave phenomena are more common than you ever thought.</span></span></span></p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><b><span lang=\"EN-US\">Reference books</span></b><span lang=\"EN-US\">:</span></span></span></p><ol><li style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 36pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Waves (In SI Units): Berkeley Physics Course Volume 3, F. S. Crawford, Jr., McGraw-Hill, 2017.</span></span></span></li><li style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 36pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Vibrations and Waves (MIT Introductory Physics Series), A. P. French, CPC Press, 2017.</span></span></span></li><li style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0.0001pt 36pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Introduction to Electrodynamics, 4<sup>th</sup> ed., David J. Griffiths, Pearson Education India, 2019.</span> </span></span></li></ol><p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0.0001pt\"> </p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"text-align: justify; margin: 0cm 0cm 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Assessment of performance will be based on quizzes(20%), assignments(20%), mid-sem exam (20%),end-sem exam(40%).</span></span></span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span style=\"color:#333333\">Attendance is mandatory. </span></span></span></span></p></div></div>",
