            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>This class will introduce students to some of the major topics in the study of contemporary metaphysics: persistence, material constitution, time, possibility and necessity, and social<br>kinds. In particular, we will focus on the way these issues bear on who we are and what we are like. Together, we will explore questions like: Are you and your child self the same<br>person? Is there an object made up of all the members of our class? What does it mean to have a disability? Is there something special about your present self and do your past and<br>futures selves exist? Could you have been different than the way you are? How different? Can games change us? Can thinking about metaphysics?</p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Grading Rubric:<br>Initial reflection/final reflection (2 x 2.5%) - 5%<br>In-class quizzes/activities - 25%<br>Midterm exam - 20%<br>Final exam - 22.5%<br>Outline/proposal for paper/project - 5%<br>Paper/Project - 22.5%</span></span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">Attendance does not officially count for your grade but 25% of your grade will come from regular in-class quizzes/activities. I will not count your 4 lowest in-class quiz/activity grades.</span></span></p></div></div>",
