            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>What role does introspection, and self-knowledge more broadly, play in mental self-regulation? Course readings include selections from the Buddhist canon, Kant, substantial portions of Maria Heim's \"The Forefunner of All Things: Buddhaghosa on Mind, Intention, and Agency\" and Quassim Cassam's \"Self-Knowledge for Humans\", in addition to selected articles. The course will be run as a seminar. Course requirements will include written discussion questions due before the start of each class, a detailed outline for a the term paper, and a 5000-word term paper. </p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Will be posted on the syllabus. </p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Will be posted on the syllabus.</p></div></div>",
