            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0cm\"> </p><p style=\"margin:0cm\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Cambria,serif\">The course will focus on issues related to Economic and Social networks. I am aware that First year MA students will be studying game theory during this semester.  This has been taken into account in the design of the course.  Some elementary graph-theoretic concepts will also be used, but no prior knowledge will be assumed.   However, some familiarity with matrix algebra, elementary probability and calculus will be assumed. </span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0cm\"> </p><p style=\"margin:0cm\"> </p><p style=\"margin:0cm\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Cambria,serif\">I hope to cover the following topics, though not necessarily in the order listed below. </span></span></p><ol><li style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Cambria,serif\">Introduction : why study networks; graph-theoretic concept, s</span></span><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Cambria,serif\">ome network characteristics. </span></span></li><li style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Cambria,serif\">Strategic Network Formation, </span></span></li><li style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Cambria,serif\">Games on Networks</span></span></li><li style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0cm 36pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Cambria,serif\">Some applications : infrastructure networks,  trading in networks, </span></span><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Cambria,serif\">   conflict and networks , diffusion, financial contagion.  </span></span></li></ol></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0cm\"> </p><p style=\"margin:0cm\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Cambria,serif\">There is no textbook for the course. Some of the material that I will cover is available in </span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0cm\"> </p><p style=\"margin:0cm\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Cambria,serif\">Matt Jackson : <i>Social and Economic Networks</i> </span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0cm\"> </p><p style=\"margin:0cm\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Cambria,serif\">I also strongly recommend  Jackson\u2019s book <i>The Human Network</i>.  This is a non-technical discussion of many of the main topics of current research.  I will also distribute lecture notes and mention other references as we go along.  </span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0cm\"> </p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>There will be a mid term exam with weight 50%, and either some asignments or a final exam worth 50%. I will decide this after week 2.</p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>I have no formal attendance requirenment. </p></div></div>",
