            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0cm\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Adobe Garamond Pro&quot;\"><b><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Abadi MT Condensed Light&quot;,sans-serif\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Course description:</span></b></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0cm\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Adobe Garamond Pro&quot;\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Abadi MT Condensed Light&quot;,sans-serif\" lang=\"EN-GB\">This course functions as a \u201claboratory\u201d for working writers of fiction. It will follow a studio format where each student takes turns to submit a piece of fiction that the class will workshop when they meet. Each submission is limited to 1,500-3,000 words. We will also be reading a series of short novellas through the semester to instigate class discussion on craft and literary technique. </span></span></span></p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0cm\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Adobe Garamond Pro&quot;\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Abadi MT Condensed Light&quot;,sans-serif\" lang=\"EN-GB\">30% = Class participation + Peer Feedback: I want you to be attentive, present and engaged. Remaining absent during workshop days for your peers will bring your down your grade significantly.</span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0cm\"> </p><p style=\"margin:0cm\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Adobe Garamond Pro&quot;\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Abadi MT Condensed Light&quot;,sans-serif\" lang=\"EN-GB\">50% = Final portfolio comprising a fiction piece (maximum 8,000 words) </span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0cm\"> </p><p style=\"margin:0cm\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Adobe Garamond Pro&quot;\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Abadi MT Condensed Light&quot;,sans-serif\" lang=\"EN-GB\">20% = Workshop Critique Packs: You will submit a critique (minimum one page) for TWO stories at the end of semester. I will review these to give you a grade. Your critiques will be written for the penultimate round of workshops conducted after midterm break.</span></span></span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0cm\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Adobe Garamond Pro&quot;\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Abadi MT Condensed Light&quot;,sans-serif\" lang=\"EN-GB\">You are allowed up to TWO absences in the semester. Further absences will incur a .5 grade cut per absence. </span></span></span></p></div></div>",
