            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Gentium Book Basic&quot;\">The theatre is a memory machine, dreamscape, courtroom, pageant, arena, living room, and hall of debate rolled into one\u2014remembering, imagining, interrogating, entertaining, reflecting, feeling, and deliberating through shared experience. In this course, we will appreciate and critique the theatre as an indispensable part of life in the modern world that can help us understand, engage, endure, and perhaps even transform the world we live in today. We will explore elements important to the theatre\u2014action, speech, character, mise en sc\u00e8ne, acting, writing, directing, devising\u2014and see how they work performances within historical contexts. If Covid and campus conditions allow, this course will include theatre workshops.  </span></span></p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>TBD</p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>TBD</p></div></div>",
