            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\">Tuaght by Anurupa Roy</span></p><p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\">What does material communicate on stage or in a performance space? What is the language of dead material? What happens when the camera interacts with material? Thus together we will explore the space between technique and improvisation, realism and abstraction, visual language and oral narratives.</span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\">The students will be introduced to performance forms where materials lead e.g Shadow puppet theatre, Material Theatre, Story boxes (Kavada), Scrolls, Paper theatre and Object Theatre. Each session will include an introduction to a form and a hands on exercise based on the form. The students will finally pick one form and create an individual creative response to the form. Also included will be a series of lectures on traditional puppet theater, contemporary puppet theater around the world and the history of animation.</span></span></span></p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\">The majority of the course work will take place in class. Hence, attendance and participation in class are the main criteria for grading. </span></span></span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Students can take up to 2 unexcused absences.</p></div></div>",
