            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><b>Course Description:</b> The Ashoka Conversation is designed as a a 200 level course to give students a hands on learning experience in conceptualizing, designing and editorial framing of a weekly digital news magazine. This is an ambitious course that seeks to put in place the structure and production of a live media resource entirely run by Ashoka Students.</p><p>Students who enroll in this course will \u2018learn on the job\u2019. Through the rigor of academic discipline and the commitment of journalistic integrity students run Open Axis- a weekly Multi-media blog project on the lines of the internationally acclaimed website \u201cThe Conversation\u201d that was set up as a non-profit network that publishes in depth news stories and content. Though the semester, students will be taught editorial decision making, ideating thematically for an issue, creating content themselves as well as commissioning articles through the University based on the specific editorial requirements for each issue.Class interactions are in the nature of editorial meetings, where students edit, write and commission articles, record podcast interviews and upload them in an organised fashion by set deadlines in rotating groups. </p><p><b>Grading and Coursework:</b> Under faculty supervision, class will be conducted on the lines of bi-weekly editorial meetings and will function as a mini-newsroom. Class participation will be at a premium when it comes to grading. Individual grades will be based on individual articles written and commissioned, and extra work in the nature of design, audio visual inputs and ideas that are brought in. </p><p>Students who take this course are expected to display excellent writing skills in terms of both flair and content. </p><p>In its fourth iteration, in Spring 2022, Open Axis will be general news website, with a focus on electoral politics. Media Studies, English, Creative Writing and Political Science students are particularly encouraged to apply. </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>The daily news. </p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>6 issues of Open Axis will be published through the semester. Each issue will be worth 15 marks, where 7 marks will be a group grade- 5 for overall editorial of the issue, 2 marks for social media promotions,</p><p>8 marks will be individual grades- 3 marks for successful commissions and 5 for independent articles. </p><p>The class of 15 students will be divided into 3 editorial groups. Individual grades will be assigned to 4 out of the 6 issues, and group grades for 2- for each individual student. </p><p>The remaining 10 marks will be for attendance.</p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>students will not be allowed more than 2 unexcused absences for the semester. Editorial meetings are crucial for newsrooms, and must not be taken lightly. </p></div></div>",
