            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><meta charset=\"UTF-8\">Thesis Workshop II is open only to students who have take Thesis Workshop I in Anthropology and Sociology. It is intended to guide students through the process of writing up their undergraduate theses in the disciplines of Anthropology and Sociology. If you have any questions about your eligibility for the course please contact the instructor directly at durba.chattaraj@ashoka.edu.in</p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>To be discussed when syllabus is distributed </p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>7 free absences, after which there will be a .5 reduction in the final letter grade per absence. The only exception to this rule is in the case of documented and severe emergencies. </p></div></div>",
