            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>The workshop will guide students through different stages after the completion of a draft manuscript. These include structural edits, manuscript  revision, line-editing, and pitching. The idea is also to develop a clear understanding of how their writing will be received by the publishing ecosystem. Hands-on exercises, presentations of students' work, and feedback from and interactions with visiting publishing editors will be part of the course.<br><br>This course is mandatory for those completing their creative writing theses, and is open only to them.</p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>The final thesis will be graded.</p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Attendance will be taken. Three absences are permitted without an impact on grades. Anything beyond this will need explanations. </p></div></div>",
