            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-2b97e0e8-7fff-03ca-34e8-7dab5a0d4f09\">Music and Cognition will introduce students to key questions across topics of research interest in the field, including music and evolution, music and development, music and emotion, music and nonmusical cognitive abilities, performing and composing music, and listening to and liking music. Students will learn to read and synthesise the scientific literature in the field, ask questions critically, and clearly communicate key findings to researchers and general audiences. </b></p><p> </p><p dir=\"ltr\"> </p><ul><li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\"> </li></ul><p><br> </p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-2b97e0e8-7fff-03ca-34e8-7dab5a0d4f09\">At the end of this course, you will:</b></p><ul><li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-2b97e0e8-7fff-03ca-34e8-7dab5a0d4f09\">Become familiar with many key questions that researchers are trying to answer in the field.</b></p></li><li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-2b97e0e8-7fff-03ca-34e8-7dab5a0d4f09\">Be able to critically read and discuss research in the field of music and cognition.</b></p></li><li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-2b97e0e8-7fff-03ca-34e8-7dab5a0d4f09\">Begin to generate research questions within the field of music and cognition.</b></p></li><li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-2b97e0e8-7fff-03ca-34e8-7dab5a0d4f09\">Improve your ability to communicate scientific questions and findings effectively to a general audience.</b></p></li></ul></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-cde6a0a2-7fff-628e-3cf5-3d6e3727f66e\">Textbook: Margulis, E. H. (2018). The psychology of music: A very short introduction. Oxford University Press. </b></p><p><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-cde6a0a2-7fff-628e-3cf5-3d6e3727f66e\">Additional weekly readings: each week, students will also read one or two additional scientific review or empirical articles. </b></p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Progress in this course will be assessed using open-book quizzes and a group podcast project with submissions spread over the term. Detailed grading rubrics will be provided to students in the course syllabus.</p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>This is a fully online course. Attendance will be taken at the begninning and end of each class, and will contribute towards the student's final grade.</p></div></div>",
