            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>This course introduces you to the theory and practice of remote sensing. Pre-requisites include my GIS I class or testing out of GIS requirements. It aims to teach through experience and expects that students will be able to conduct their own mini-projects by the end of the course. By the end of the course, you should have the theoretical background to understand remote sensing processes and apply them using ENVI (I already introduced you to GEE, and that requires this theoretical knowledge to compile your own codes).</p><p>Detailed syllabus attached. </p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>By the end of the course, you should have the theoretical background to understand remote sensing processes and apply them using ENVI (I already introduced you to GEE, and that requires this theoretical knowledge to compile your own codes).</p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Since, this is a 300-level course, I have designed the course so that your out-of-class work load will be about 3-4 hours per week (+ depending on the final project you choose to do).</p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0cm; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin-right:0cm; margin-left:0cm\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Students will be graded on 4 metrics:</span></span></span></span></span></p><ol><li style=\"margin-top:0cm; margin-right:0cm; margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Class attendance and participation: 15% of grade</span></span></span></span></span></li><li style=\"margin-top:0cm; margin-right:0cm; margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Assignments (35% of grade): We will learn a particular skill every Friday which will be related to the lecture on Thursday. This will be in the form of a class assignment, to be done in class as much as possible, and to be submitted as a pdf prior to subsequent class on Thursday. I expect you to be able to complete this in the Friday class itself. If not, it should not take much extra time. </span></span></span></span></span></li><li style=\"margin-top:0cm; margin-right:0cm; margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Quizzes (15% of grade): Quizzes will test your understanding of concepts. They will require you to keep up with reading the textbook. I will not ask you detailed questions on the quizzes like a CBSE exam but larger concepts. </span></span></span></span></span></li><li style=\"margin-top:0cm; margin-right:0cm; margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Final project (35% of grade): This project can be done individually or in a group. We will discuss in class what we want to do. If we choose a group project, we can do something with enough rigour to add to the body of knowledge. </span></span></span></span></span></li></ol><p style=\"margin-top:0cm; margin-right:0cm; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin-left:36.0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">The grading of the projected is distributed as:</span></span></span></span></span></p><ol style=\"list-style-type:lower-alpha\"><li style=\"margin-top:0cm; margin-right:0cm; margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Presentation of project/research question (5%) in the 10<sup>th</sup> week</span></span></span></span></span></li><li style=\"margin-top:0cm; margin-right:0cm; margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Work on project (5%)</span></span></span></span></span></li><li style=\"margin-top:0cm; margin-right:0cm; margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Final project presentation (5% + an additional 5% peer grading)</span></span></span></span></span></li><li style=\"margin-top:0cm; margin-right:0cm; margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Final write-up (15%): The final write-up must include sections Introduction, Methods, Maps, Results, Discussion, References (at least 5 references)</span></span></span></span></span></li></ol> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Students can miss a maximum of 4 classes excluded excused absences, beyond which they will get a failing grade. All excused absences must be routed to me through the OAA.</p></div></div><div><strong>Attachment</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><table><tbody><tr><td><a style=\"color:blue\" href=\"https://ams.ashoka.edu.in/UploadFiles/CourseCatalogueFiles/779832d8-4bd7-46fd-aff7-dd3ffe6db71d.pdf\" download=\"Syllabus Remote Sensing 2022.pdf\">Syllabus Remote Sensing 2022.pdf</a></td></tr></tbody></table></div></div>",
