            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Chemistry in Everyday Life , Examples and Historical Perspectives ( 1 Lecture)</p><p>States of Matter ( 1 Lecture)</p><p>Principle of Chemical Thermodynamics and Kinetics ( 1 Lecture)</p><p>Periodic Table ( 1 Lecture)</p><p>Chemical Bond- The heart of Chemistry; Covalent, coordination, ionic and hydrogen bonds ( 1 Lecture)</p><p>Octate Rules (1 Lecture)</p><p>Bohr's model  of hydrogen atom (1 Lecture)</p><p>Basic principles of quantum mechanics ( 1 Lecture)</p><p>Concept of Stationary states ( 1 lecture)</p><p>Particle-in-a box, Harmonic oscillator ( 2 Lectures)</p><p>Quantum mechancal description of hydrogen atom- Orbitals (1 Lecture)</p><p>Atoms to Molecules MO and VB theory - Concept of hybridisation ( 2 Lectures)</p><p>Huckel Theory ( 1 Lecture)</p><p>Basic Organic chemistry, catenation property  1 Lecture)</p><p>Basic Synthesis of Organic molecules ( 2 Lectures)</p><p>Hybridisation and shapes of molecules (2 Lectures)</p><p>Electrophilicity and nucleophilicity ( 1 Lecture)</p><p>C-C, C=C and C C triple bonds ( 1 Lecture)</p><p>Basic principles of inorganic and coordination chemistry (2 Lectures)</p><p>Chemical biology- An overview (1 Lecture)</p><p>Chemistry of Materials- An overview ( 1 Lecture)</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Expected to learn basic chemistry and develop interests</p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Basic interest and FC course of 0801-3 ( preferred)</p><p>General Chemistry Text books</p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Will be discused in the class</p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p> 70 percent</p></div></div>",
