            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">In this course, you will be introduced to the wonders of chemistry practicals. You will receive comprehensive training on applying chemical knowledge in solving real-life problems. At the end of the semester, you will be in a position to explore the advance level chemistry world.</span></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">You will receive hands-on training in the experiments below</span></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">1. <meta charset=\"utf-8\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-9096e810-7fff-1ebd-6c65-47649b791ad1\">Study of the viscosity of the unknown liquid (glycerol, sugar) with respect to water</b></span></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">2. <meta charset=\"utf-8\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-ed6c49b8-7fff-cc69-4429-2d20f50bf511\">Verification of Beer and Lambert\u2019s Law for KMnO4 and K2Cr2O7 solution</b></span></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">3. <meta charset=\"utf-8\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-d3118d6c-7fff-6e74-4afe-14c79f6e33e8\">Solid-state synthesis of benzilic acid from benzil</b></span></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-d3118d6c-7fff-6e74-4afe-14c79f6e33e8\">4. Transesterification of vegetable oil to produce bio-diesel</b></span></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">5. S<b id=\"docs-internal-guid-8ede3efb-7fff-ce09-3a0e-a973aca7261a\">pectroscopic study of DNA-ligand interaction and binding analysis</b></span></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">6. Extraction of caffeine from tea leaves</span></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">7. <span style=\"line-height:107%\">Determination of the pH of Hair Shampoo</span></span></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\">8. <span style=\"line-height:107%\">Determination of water Hardness with EDTA</span></span></span></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\">9. </span>To study the kinetics of inversion of cane sugar</span></span></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\">10. Estimation of Calcium content in milk</span></span></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\">11. </span>Conductometric titration of strong acid and strong base</span></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">12. ionic strength determination using conductometer</span></span></strong></p><p><strong><span style=\"font-size:12px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">13. Purification of an organic compound by crystalization</span></span></strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Hands on training in handling chemicals</p><p>Hands on training in operating instruments</p><p>Hands on training in analytical, quantitative, and qualitative experiments</p><p> </p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>No prerequisite </p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>25% class attendance and engagements</p><p>25% Practical notebook</p><p>40% Assignments/exam</p><p>10% Oral exam</p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>75%</p></div></div>",
