            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0in 0in 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">This course is mainly designed to understand various reagents used in the synthesis of biomolecule conjugates without interfering with native biochemical processes (biorthogonal chemistry). The basic spectroscopic methods like Infrared (IR) and UV-visible will also be taught to determine the structures of bioconjugates. </span></span></span></span></p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">After the completion of this course, students could be able to extend their knowledge to synthetic biology, connecting fluorescent probes to biomolecules, organic and inorganic molecules, and could use basic spectroscopic methods to analyze the products. This could be a very interesting course to do magical transformations in the biomolecules to understand biochemical processes and develop diagnostic tools.</span></span></span></p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">This course does require a basic understanding of organic chemistry. However, students without any background knowledge will be offered 2-3 hours one to one discussion sessions to bridge the learning gaps. The course material (refs, ppt presentations, videos) will be shared with students during the classes.</span></span></span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0in 0in 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Seminars, review writing, assignments, and quizzes will be assigned to enhance the understanding  of the subject and interest as well.  However,  the final grading and assessment format will be discussed at the beginning of the course.</span></span></span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0in 0in 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">This is mainly an online course and attendance is required as per Ashoka University policy.</span></span></span></p></div></div>",
