            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Garamond&quot;,serif\">ENG-2410-1 Critical Thinking Seminar: Caste Creativity <i>Valan </i></span></span></span></b></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom:0cm; margin-top:0cm; margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Garamond&quot;,serif\">TR 10:10-11:40</span></span></span></b></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom:0cm; margin-top:0cm; margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Garamond&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">In this course we will look at texts across genre/media\u2014novels, short stories, essays, poetry, films\u2014and ask the following questions: What do these texts tell us about caste? How do they erase caste while telling us something else? If caste isn't explicitly mentioned, what are the tools we may use to understand the caste action at play? Is caste a religious issue? If it is, is it particular only to Hinduism? Can we read for caste only through the lens of identity? We will encounter texts that are immediately identifiable as dealing with issues concerning caste, and those that--with some prodding\u2014show us the many insidious ways in which caste configures our lives. This is a writing-intensive course.</span></span></span></span></span> </span></span></span></p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>This is a CTS.  You will be expected to workshop drafts of your essays, and improve your skills as a critical academic writer.</p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>A-F</p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Attendance is expected in every class as this is a small seminar with an emphasis on groupwork</p></div></div>",
