            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\">Taught by Achintya Prahlad</span></p><p> </p><p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\">This course is focussed on shringaara - loosely translated as the romantic or erotic element - in Sanskrit poetry. It will discuss works such as Kalidasa's romantic poetry including the Meghadutam and the shringaara-laden verses that appear in his plays such as the Shakuntalam, Jayadeva's Gita Govindam, the romantic poetry within the Ramayana, verses of Bhartrhari, and so on. There will also be a discussion of the general imagery used in shringaara poetry - Kamadeva's flower arrows, birds such as the chakora and chakravaaka, the seasons, etc. Students will also learn about Sanskrit poetic meters. No prior knowledge of Sanskrit is required for this course, since all verses discussed will be translated.</span></span></span></p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\">The majority of the course work will take place in class. Hence, attendance and participation in class are the main criteria for grading. </span></span></span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\">Students can take up to 2 unexcused absences.</span></p></div></div>",
