            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\">Taught by Sudha Raghuraman</span></p><p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\">Ancient South Indian treatises on music liken the swaras or musical notes to the sounds of nature, andgo on to describe humankind's efforts to simulate these sounds through music. Purandaradasa is referred to as the parent of Carnatic music. He is credited with the beginner's songs used for learning.These basic lessons are the building blocks for more advanced performance forms like alapana, neraval and swara prastara.</span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\">This course will take the students through the history of carnatic music as well as its foundational lessons, which will include- saralivarisai, jantavarisai and geetham along with an exploration of melodic patterns and talam or rhythmic structures.</span></span></span></p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\">The majority of the course work will take place in class. Hence, attendance and participation in class are the main criteria for grading. </span></span></span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\">Students can take up to 2 unexcused absences.</span></p></div></div>",
