            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\">Taught by Kriti M Pant</span></p><p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\">The relationship between theatre and ritual is a complex one spanning millennia. There are as many rituals as there are narratives, ideologies, cultures and, indeed, theatrical traditions. But do such acts speak to us even today?</span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\">In this course, students will discover how sacred and secular ritual forms have and continue to influence contemporary theatre practices. Through improvisation, collaborative devising, and theatre games and exercises that draw on psychophysical praxis, they will grapple with questions like \u2013 What is a ritual? How can the power of ritual awaken, challenge and nourish the actor\u2019s inner life? Can the physical enactment of ritual transform perception and presence? What can theatre practice offer us in an uncertain, rapidly evolving world like ours? Students will also develop their own individual and collective rituals based on personal inquiry into their own lived experiences, creative impulses and immediate needs.</span></span></span></p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Georgia&quot;,serif\">The majority of the course work will take place in class. Hence, attendance and participation in class are the main criteria for grading. </span></span></span></span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\">Students can take up to 2 unexcused absences.</span></p></div></div>",
