            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\">Taught by Manishikha Baul</span></p><p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\">This course is designed to introduce Odissi, an Indian traditional dance form, through the various complex perspectives of living in contemporary times in India. Instead of focusing on learning the form as it has been, carried forward and handed over to new learners by Gurus, dancers, teachers and experts over decades, it attempts to find points of entry and points of departure through the body (or collective bodies) located in the present socio-political and cultural context. We try to navigate queries like 'what would be the negotiations of a body to embody Odissi'? By large, mitigating our fears, challenges and curiosity of the \"Indian Classical Dance Forms' become a crucial aspect of this negotiation. The sessions are physical, playful, choreographic, tactile, devised and theoretical in nature. This course does not require you to have any previous knowledge, skill or body practice. </span></span></span></p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Georgia&quot;,serif\">The majority of the course work will take place in class. Hence, attendance and participation in class are the main criteria for grading. </span></span></span></span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Students can take up to 2 unexcused absences. </p></div></div>",
