            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\">Taught by Abhinaya Penneswaran</span></p><p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\">This course will approach movement- dance as well as general body language- through the lens of composition. Students will learn performance and movement techniques from Contemporary Dance, Bharatanatyam and Yoga. Exploration in class will involve understanding the visual impact of a body creating shapes- in dynamic motion, in rest and everything in between. Students will be encouraged to configure a vocabulary of movement that their body understands and is comfortable with, using abstraction and meaning-making as contrasting tools. We will try and find ways to acknowledge bodily impulse and the effect of music and text on our exploration methods.  We will learn how to string movement and gestures together, as a means of expression, for performance, or just for a sense of release.  Students do not require prior training in any form of dance to enroll in this course. </span></span></span></p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\">The majority of the course work will take place in class. Hence, attendance and participation in class are the main criteria for grading. </span></span></span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\">Students can take up to 2 unexcused absences.</span></p></div></div>",
