            "document":"",
            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\">Taught by Dinesh Khanna</span></p><p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\">The best camera is the one with you. And which is the one that is always, well mostly, with us? The mobile phone camera, of course. So that takes care of the hardware. And what do we do with it? Take pictures, snaps, clicks, captures, selfies, et al. And what do these represent? A haphazard and largely incoherent account of our lives. However, our days and our lives have so many interesting incidents which when strung together would make for really interesting stories to tell, share and preserve.</span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\">Now consider this. The number of images shot and shared every day is believed to be over 2 billion. Yes, every day. On the negative side, one can feel that's like a tsunami which we all are drowning in. However, on the positive side, one can say that the most used language today is photography. And we are all fluent in the language but tend to be rather flippant and chaotic in using it. The idea of this course is to understand how to approach image-making and storytelling in a more mindful and purposeful manner in order to create a visual journal of our lives and matters that interest us, using photographs, words, feelings and maybe, even music.</span></span></span></p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\">The majority of the course work will take place in class. Hence, attendance and participation in class are the main criteria for grading. </span></span></span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\">Students can take up to 2 unexcused absences.</span></p></div></div>",
