            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\">Taught by Ruchika Wason Singh</span></p><p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\">This course will engage with the idea of story sharing by playing with the format of paper. As opposed to a static two-dimensional sheet of paper, the participants will use paper as a scroll or a book with folds (like the Chinese-folding book). The entire space of the scroll and the folding book will be used to create. An important part of this course will be the idea of sharing a story by choosing what to show and what not to show to the viewer. This will also allow for the play between the folds of the book to form combinations, making it viable for display. The painted book and the scroll will be more like painted objects rather than just painted surfaces. These participants could use paint, do collage, and draw to express themselves. </span></span></span></p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\">The majority of the course work will take place in class. Hence, attendance and participation in class are the main criteria for grading. </span></span></span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\">Students can take up to 2 unexcused absences.</span></p></div></div>",
