            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\">Taught by Dorothee Gieux</span></p><p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\">This course will take you through emblematic and lesser known francophone comic books and graphic novels, which constitute the 9<sup>th</sup> Art. In this journey, you will dive into the rich history of France, made alive through the illustrations of 20<sup>th</sup> and 21<sup>st</sup> century artists, and learn basic colloquial French in an easy and lively manner, through materials that combine authentic dialogues and the powerful emotion of images. </span></span></span></p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 8pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\">The majority of the course work will take place in class. Hence, attendance and participation in class are the main criteria for grading. </span></span></span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\">Students can take up t 2 unexcused absences.</span></p></div></div>",
