            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0cm\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\" lang=\"EN-GB\">The goal of this module is to introduce the students to the concepts of landscape ecology, and to the understanding of processes relevant to the study of species and ecosystems in heterogeneous landscapes, and the conservation of species, ecosystems and processes at the scale of landscapes. </span></span></span></span></p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0cm\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\" lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">At the end of this module, the students would be introduced to concepts related to: (1) Foundations and research methods in landscape ecology, (2) Descriptions of heterogeneous landscapes, (3) Processes relevant to large landscapes, and the concept of scale, (4) Dispersal and connectivity, and (5) Spatial conservation planning.</span></span></p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0cm\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Students should have a basic understanding of ecology, and some working knowledge of QGIS and R. We will not follow a textbook, but readings will be provided in class. </span></span></span></span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0cm\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Lab exercises: 30</span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0cm\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Project: 30</span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0cm\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Class participation: 10</span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0cm\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Exam: 30</span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0cm\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Total: 100</span></span></span></span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0cm\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Same as Ashoka\u2019s general attendance policy</span></span></span></span></p></div></div>",
