            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>This course aims to introduce students to key events and important developments in the history of Pakistan. It seeks to bring students to reflect on the significance of these events by engaging with historiographical debates about the country\u2019s political trajectory. Organized thematically, the course not only focuses on political matters but also intends to familiarize students with broader societal and cultural changes that took place in Pakistan since the country\u2019s independence. Students will be invited to read and discuss primary sources.</p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Course prerequisites: Introduction to Comparative Politics or Introduction to Indian Politics.</p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Details about grading wil be provided at a later stage.</p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Attendance is mandatory, apart from four grace absences. Ten percent of the total final grade will be based on attendance. Students who have attended at least 22 of the 26 sessions will get the full 10%; those who attended 21 or less of the 26 sessions will not get any marks for attendance.</p></div></div>",
