            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>We wil study calculus of functions between normed linear spaces. Special emphasis will be given to functions of matrices.</p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>A good undrstanding of calculus from an advanced viewpoint. A preparation for courses on nonlinear analysis, calculus on manifolds, matrix functions.</p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Students must have taken the following courses:</p><p>Multivariable calculus.</p><p>Linear Algebra and Matrix Analysis</p><p>Metic and Topological Spaces</p><p>The course on Functional Analysis is desirable but not necessary.</p><p>References:</p><p>1. J. Dieudonne, Foundations of Modern Analysis, Academic Press</p><p>2. Kalyan Mukherjea, Differential Calculus in Normed Linear Spaces, TRIM Series, Hindustan Book Agency</p><p>3. Rodney Coleman, Calculus on Normed Vector Spaces, Universitext, Springer</p><p> </p><p> </p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Will be discussed in class.</p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Regular attndance is encouraged.</p></div></div>",
