            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0cm; text-align:start; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif\"><span style=\"caret-color:#000000\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\"><span style=\"font-variant-caps:normal\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"letter-spacing:normal\"><span style=\"text-transform:none\"><span style=\"white-space:normal\"><span style=\"word-spacing:0px\"><span style=\"text-decoration:none\">As Uttar Pradesh gears towards its 18<sup>th</sup> state election, this course will at the same time a deep dive into the political history of India\u2019s political heartland, a study of a campaign in real time and an introduction to the art of electoral analysis. We will cover the history of party formation and of their electoral performance, the transformation of Uttar Pradesh\u2019s party system, the successive phases of electoral politics that have shaped not only the politics of UP but of the country at large. We will also cover the sociology of parties, elected representatives and candidates and the transformations of electoral politics. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0cm; text-align:start; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px\"> </p><p style=\"margin:0cm; text-align:start; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif\"><span style=\"caret-color:#000000\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\"><span style=\"font-variant-caps:normal\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"letter-spacing:normal\"><span style=\"text-transform:none\"><span style=\"white-space:normal\"><span style=\"word-spacing:0px\"><span style=\"text-decoration:none\">Though not primarily a data-driven course, a special emphasis will be brought to the use of data in the study of state politics. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0cm; text-align:start; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px\"> </p><p style=\"margin:0cm; text-align:start; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri, sans-serif\"><span style=\"caret-color:#000000\"><span style=\"color:#000000\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\"><span style=\"font-variant-caps:normal\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"letter-spacing:normal\"><span style=\"text-transform:none\"><span style=\"white-space:normal\"><span style=\"word-spacing:0px\"><span style=\"text-decoration:none\">The course will contain a variety of assignments, including (among other things) maintaining a campaign journal, profiling marginal players and writing a book review.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>This course will familiarize you with the basics of electoral analysis, including the interpretation and the contectualization of data. It will also enhance your ability to think critically about party and electoral politics. </p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>TBD</p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>As long as we are offline, no more than three absences. Attendance is otherwise mandatory. </p></div></div>",
