            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-0d947ea3-7fff-38f3-446a-3a748d312ab3\">It matters what stories we tell to tell other stories with; it matters what knots knot knots, what thoughts think thoughts, what descriptions describe descriptions, what ties tie ties.(Haraway, 2016)</b></p><p> </p><p dir=\"ltr\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-0d947ea3-7fff-38f3-446a-3a748d312ab3\">If  \u2018worlding\u2019 refers to the summoning of new ways of being of  in the present,  words pluralize any singular worlding from a comparative perspective. Reformulations of the anthropocene such as the  chuthulucene, plantationocene, capitalocene, Shivacene, and many more speak from particular time and space. Adjacent concepts modify the universe with the pluriverse and the multiverse, politics with cosmopolitics or juxtapose the globe and the planet. To give another example, the human is amended by the non-human, the post-human, the inhuman, the unhuman as well as with other-than-human persons through practices that seek to express the divergent. And beyond such worldings, the present ecological crisis casts the decimation of the indigenes in the Americas as the first extinction where the \u2018end of the world\u2019 has already happened - an invitation to think the future through non-western-centric constructions and revised genealogies.</b></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-0d947ea3-7fff-38f3-446a-3a748d312ab3\">The focus of the course will be to analyse the significance of contemporary concepts so as to learn how to evaluate and sculpt concepts that reflect difference. </b></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-0d947ea3-7fff-38f3-446a-3a748d312ab3\">We will draw on a selection of worldings from Donna Haraway, Isabelle Stengers, Dipesh Chakrabarty, Bruno Latour,  Viveiros de Castro , Marilyn Strathern, Philippe Descola, Eduardo Kohn and Michel Foucault and will attempt to orient the readings to students\u2019 research interests. </b></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-0d947ea3-7fff-38f3-446a-3a748d312ab3\">Students from MLS are welcome!</b></p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>TBD</p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>TBD</p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>TBD</p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>TBD</p></div></div>",
