            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,&quot;sans-serif&quot;\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;\">What is cinema? This classic question posed by early film theory will guide our survey of theoretical approaches to the study of film from its beginnings in the 1910s to the present. We will study major film theories such as the realist film theory, formalist film theory, auteur theory, feminist film theory, apparatus theory, semiotics and psychoanalytic film theory but also turn to film-philosophical approaches to cinema. <span style=\"background:white\">We will be discussing the debates and arguments that have shaped film studies and situate film theory in the context of larger intellectual movements such as Phenomenology, Russian Formalism, Marxism, Existentialism and Poststructuralism. We will discuss </span>the major film theories in relation to different film genres, film movements and national cinemas. Film theorists studied will include Hugo Munsterberg, B<span style=\"background:white\">\u00e9</span>la Bal<span style=\"background:white\">\u00e1</span>zs, Walter Benjamin, Rudolph Arnheim, Sergei Eisenstein, Siegfried Kracauer, Andre Bazin, Jean-Louis Baudry, Christian Metz, Laura Mulvey and Gilles Deleuze. Film screenings will include the works of Sergei Eisenstein, Chris Marker, Terrence Malick, Max Ophuls, Abbas Kiarostami, Paul Thomas Anderson, Agnes Varda, Ang Lee and Chang-dong Lee. Students who opt for this course must be familiar with basic terms and concepts in film studies (such as montage, mise-en-sc<span style=\"background:white\">\u00e8</span>ne, continuity editing) or have taken an introductory course in film studies.</span></span></span></span></span></p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Grading rubric TBA.</p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Attendance policy TBA.</p></div></div>",
