            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-2a0c0795-7fff-84d9-43b2-a2ae72ae2b65\">Introduction to Still Photography (Introductory Course)</b></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-2a0c0795-7fff-84d9-43b2-a2ae72ae2b65\">Course Cap: 15 Students</b></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-2a0c0795-7fff-84d9-43b2-a2ae72ae2b65\">Course Code: MS-1012</b></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-2a0c0795-7fff-84d9-43b2-a2ae72ae2b65\">Course Faculty: A K Ranjit/Maya Mirchandani </b></p><p> </p><p dir=\"ltr\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-2a0c0795-7fff-84d9-43b2-a2ae72ae2b65\">This course is divided into two parts. First is a critical appreciation segment of image histories by Professor Maya Mirchandani, who will introduce us to several ways of looking at images (6 Classes before mid-term). The rest of the semester classes will be held by Professor Ranjit. </b></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-2a0c0795-7fff-84d9-43b2-a2ae72ae2b65\">`Introduction to Still Photography\u2019 course is designed to cover six fundamentals of photography including Light, Subject, Optics, Aperture, Time and Recording Medium. Here, both practical and theoretical teaching in digital technologies will provide a path to explore knowledge and have hands-on experience in photography. You will learn, how cameras work like shutter speed, aperture, composition and more in this course curriculum.  Hand-on sessions with important photography concepts along with short quizzes will help in building your confidence in building up your creative ideas.   </b></p><p> </p><p dir=\"ltr\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-2a0c0795-7fff-84d9-43b2-a2ae72ae2b65\">Course Content</b></p><p> </p><ol><li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-2a0c0795-7fff-84d9-43b2-a2ae72ae2b65\">How does a camera work?</b></p></li><li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-2a0c0795-7fff-84d9-43b2-a2ae72ae2b65\">What is Exposure in Photography?</b></p></li><li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-2a0c0795-7fff-84d9-43b2-a2ae72ae2b65\">Shutter Speed</b></p></li><li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-2a0c0795-7fff-84d9-43b2-a2ae72ae2b65\">Camera Focus</b></p></li><li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-2a0c0795-7fff-84d9-43b2-a2ae72ae2b65\">Aperture and Depth of Field</b></p></li><li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-2a0c0795-7fff-84d9-43b2-a2ae72ae2b65\">Get Creative in Manual Mode</b></p></li><li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-2a0c0795-7fff-84d9-43b2-a2ae72ae2b65\">Optics and Lenses</b></p></li><li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-2a0c0795-7fff-84d9-43b2-a2ae72ae2b65\">The Recording Medium</b></p></li><li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-2a0c0795-7fff-84d9-43b2-a2ae72ae2b65\">Composition</b></p></li><li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-2a0c0795-7fff-84d9-43b2-a2ae72ae2b65\">Practice different types of composition/framing using various lighting techniques and use of lenses. Taking photographs outdoor &amp; indoors.</b></p></li><li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-2a0c0795-7fff-84d9-43b2-a2ae72ae2b65\">Dynamic landscape photography both day and night.</b></p></li><li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-2a0c0795-7fff-84d9-43b2-a2ae72ae2b65\">Basic Interface of Photoshop \u2013 Basic Tools &amp; Functions</b></p></li><li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-2a0c0795-7fff-84d9-43b2-a2ae72ae2b65\">The Essentials of Camera Raw -<br>How to Open Different Types of Images in Camera Raw, Applying a Camera Profile, Using Camera Raw Like It\u2019s a Filter, Setting the White Balance, Seeing a Before/After in Camera Raw</b></p></li><li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-2a0c0795-7fff-84d9-43b2-a2ae72ae2b65\">Special Effects - Adding Vignetting Effects, Adding Custom Vignettes &amp; Spotlights</b></p></li><li aria-level=\"1\" dir=\"ltr\"><p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-2a0c0795-7fff-84d9-43b2-a2ae72ae2b65\">Working with Layers.</b></p></li></ol></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-72675d94-7fff-2ed8-761e-041c4ad35cc1\">This course will give you the necessary skill-set and understanding you need to make your photo\u2019s stand out from the rest in this practical guide we will focus on the artistic as well as the technical aspects of DSLR photography and how to use these basic principles to better your images.</b></p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-18fc49eb-7fff-9d9e-c3a1-447fdb434778\">A desire to express your creativity!</b></p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p dir=\"ltr\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-e09fff1b-7fff-caf8-adb2-00b181e1ed81\">Attendance &amp; Participation \u2013 25 %. </b></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-e09fff1b-7fff-caf8-adb2-00b181e1ed81\">This will include class presentations, quizzes, responding to watchlist/ reading list in class each week, as well as 10 % within this, for group work.</b></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-e09fff1b-7fff-caf8-adb2-00b181e1ed81\">Pre-midterm assignment 20 %.</b></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-e09fff1b-7fff-caf8-adb2-00b181e1ed81\">Still photography composition \u2013 basic - 25 %.</b></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><b id=\"docs-internal-guid-e09fff1b-7fff-caf8-adb2-00b181e1ed81\">The final assignment will be a Still Photographic Narrative\u2013 30%</b></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Students can miss at most two classes (1:30 each) without a grade cut. After that, the number of absences will be taken into account and will be reflected in the student's net attendance grade, which is 10% of the total.</p></div></div>",
