            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\" lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Garamond&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Literary study in the 21<sup>st</sup> century has been riven by debates about the practice of reading. Is distant reading likely to dethrone the dominant method of close reading? Will deep reading lose its primacy to new methods of surface reading? Has critique become synonymous with the hermeneutics of suspicion? Is it possible to enact affirmation in an act of critique? We plan to bring these questions to the amorphous archive of world literature in English as shaped by</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\" lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Garamond&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\"> British colonialism and Anglo-American globalization. Beginning with James Joyce\u2019s <i>Ulysses</i> and concluding with Arvind Krishna Mehrotra\u2019s 2020 <i>Book of Indian Essays</i>, we\u2019ll study the elusive symbol of world literature through some of the most urgent questions about reading, history, context, reason, and modernity. </span></span></span></span></p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0cm\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\" lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Garamond&quot;,serif\">20%</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\" lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Garamond&quot;,serif\">; Research presentation: <b>20%</b>; Midterm essay (1500 </span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\" lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Garamond&quot;,serif\">words): <b>25%</b>; Final research paper (2500 words): <b>35%</b> (5% for abstract, 30% for paper)</span></span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0cm\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\" lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Garamond&quot;,serif\">Attendance is required, and <b>20%</b> of your grade depends on the regularity of your attendance and the quality of your class participation.</span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0cm\"> </p><p><u><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\" lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Garamond&quot;,serif\">Anyone missing <b>6</b> or more class meetings will fail the course, regardless of other work completed. </span></span></u></p></div></div>",
