            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-7df17ea4-7fff-5ecf-d99b-8fb0a65e2bc4\" style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">In this course, we\u2019ll study philosophical questions about literature and read some works of literature through a philosophical lense. We\u2019ll explore philosophical questions like the following. Are there `objective facts\u2019 about beauty and literary merit (and what functions do discussions of literary merit serve)? What is the relationship between aesthetic values and other values? For example, does engaging with great works of art provide some kind of special (and especially valuable) knowledge which is impossible to communicate in other terms? Can works of art be morally misguided in a  way that counts as an aesthetic flaw? We\u2019ll read and discuss some selections from literary works by authors like Borges, Proust, Nabokov and Wilde from a philosophical point of view. </span></p><p><strong>offered by</strong>: Associate Professor Dr. Sharon Berry (incoming); <strong>mailto</strong>: seberry@invariant.org</p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>This class aims to familiarize students with some major puzzles and theories in (broadly analytic) philosophy of literature.  It also aims to improve student skills at</p><ul><li>Reading, interpreting and creatively responding to dense philosophical texts</li><li>Creating, developing and communicating original philosophical arguments.</li><li>Productive philosophical conversation</li></ul></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Readings will be posted on the course website.</p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><table width=\"500\" height=\"105\" cellspacing=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" border=\"1\"><tbody><tr><td>20%</td><td>Reading Response Activities</td></tr><tr><td>20%</td><td>Class Participation</td></tr><tr><td>30%</td><td>Midterm paper (Pitch, Draft &amp; Revision) </td></tr><tr><td>30%</td><td>Final Paper (Pitch, Draft &amp; Revision)</td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>TBA (pending COVID updates)</p></div></div>",
