            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\" lang=\"EN-GB\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">How do we go about studying animal populations, understanding factors that drive their dynamics, and assessing their spatial distribution, towards the purpose of conserving them? This course will deal with basics of (1) population ecology, including factors that lead to increases and decreases in animal population size over time; structure of populations; spatial distribution of animals; and with how we can reliably and scientifically study animal populations, covering concepts related to imperfect detection and sampling</span></span></p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0cm\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Through the course of this class, students would have understood: (1) concepts of population state and vital rates; (2) factors that lead to and shape population dynamics over time; (3) population age-sex structure; (4) spatial structure of populations; (5) methods to estimate population parameters, including occupancy modelling and capture\u2013recapture sampling. Students would have had exposure to some classic papers in the field, as well as new developments. </span></span></span></span></p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0cm\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Students should have a basic understanding of ecology, and some working knowledge of Excel, QGIS and R. We will not follow a textbook, but readings will be provided in class. </span></span></span></span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0cm\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Lab exercises: 30</span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0cm\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Project: 30</span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0cm\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Class participation: 10</span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0cm\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Exam: 30</span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0cm\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Total: 100</span></span></span></span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0cm\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:115%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\" lang=\"EN-GB\">Same as Ashoka\u2019s general attendance policy</span></span></span></span></p></div></div>",
