            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0in 0in 8pt\">The course content is modified because students in Ashoka have a multidimensional learning approach rather than the conventional uni-dimensional learning approach.</p><p style=\"margin:0in 0in 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">This course is mainly designed to understand the spectroscopic and spectrometric tools used in understanding the structure of organic/organometallic/biomolecules and could also be useful in getting deeper insight into the structure-activity relationships.  Nuclear Magnetic Resonance (NMR) and Mass spectrometry (MS) have become important methods in organic, organometallics, inorganic, biochemistry, and synthetic biology.</span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0in 0in 8pt\"> </p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">After the completion of this course, students could be able to extend their knowledge to understand the structures of small chemical and complex biological entities in synthetic biology, polymers, biochemistry, organic and inorganic chemistry, etc. </span></span></span></span></p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><font face=\"Calibri, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 14.6667px;\">In this course, basic as well as advanced spectroscopic methods will be discussed so no prior knowledge is required. The course material and reference books will be shared during the classes.</span></font></p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">Seminars, review writing, assignments, and quizzes will be assigned to enhance the understanding of the subject and interest as well.  However,  the final grading and assessment format will be discussed at the beginning of the course.</span></span></span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">This is mainly an online course and the policy of attendance will be discussed at the beginning of the course.</span></span></span></p></div></div>",
