            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin-bottom:0cm\"><span style=\"background:transparent\"><span style=\"line-height:100%\"><font face=\"Baskerville\"><font size=\"3\"><font style=\"font-size: 13pt\"><font color=\"#000000\">In November 2021, the 6</font><font color=\"#000000\"><sup>th</sup></font><font color=\"#000000\"> plenum of the 19</font><font color=\"#000000\"><sup>th</sup></font><font color=\"#000000\"> Chinese Communist Party Congress adopted only the third \u2018Historical Resolution\u2019 since the CCP\u2019s founding, and the first since 1981. </font><font color=\"#000000\">While the focus of these resolutions is </font><font color=\"#000000\">on</font><font color=\"#000000\"> defining the </font><font color=\"#000000\">p</font><font color=\"#000000\">arty\u2019s role in Chinese history since 1921, they also locate the CCP within a </font><font color=\"#000000\"><i>longue dur\u00e9e</i></font><font color=\"#000000\"> history of </font><font color=\"#000000\">the Chinese state. </font><font color=\"#000000\">These </font><font color=\"#000000\">r</font><font color=\"#000000\">esolutions point to </font><font color=\"#000000\">the significance of</font> <font color=\"#000000\">China\u2019s pre-modern history </font><font color=\"#000000\">as a source of ideas and narratives about China\u2019s present and future.</font></font></font></font></span></span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom:0cm\"><span style=\"background:transparent\"><span style=\"line-height:100%\"><font face=\"Baskerville\"><font size=\"3\"><font style=\"font-size: 13pt\"><font color=\"#000000\">Over the last four decades, </font><font color=\"#000000\">Chinese </font><font color=\"#000000\">journalists, academics, and other public intellectuals have </font><font color=\"#000000\">energetically debated </font><font color=\"#000000\">what direction China should take after the end of Cultural Revolution.</font> <font color=\"#000000\">In this class, we will explore the </font><font color=\"#000000\">contours of these debates through a focus on </font><font color=\"#000000\">history. In addition to key concepts and figures </font><font color=\"#000000\">in intellectual history, we will discuss the role of the state in shaping and restricting the scope of debate at particular times. Finally, we will extend our analysis into the ways </font><font color=\"#000000\">that </font><font color=\"#000000\">ideas about China\u2019s history play out \u2018in practice\u2019 \u2013 practices of memorialisation and display, fictionalisation and entertainment.</font></font></font></font></span></span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom:0cm\"> </p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Suggested background reading (optional):</p><p>Rana Mitter. <i>A Bitter Revolution: China's Struggle with the Modern World</i>, Oxford University Press, 2005 <a href=\"http://ebookcentral.proquest.com.elibrary.ashoka.edu.in/lib/ashoka/detail.action?docID=422670&amp;query=a+bitter+revolution\">http://ebookcentral.proquest.com.elibrary.ashoka.edu.in/lib/ashoka/detail.action?docID=422670&amp;query=a+bitter+revolution</a></p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin-bottom:0cm\"><span style=\"background:transparent\"><span style=\"line-height:100%\"><font color=\"#000000\"><font face=\"Baskerville\"><font size=\"3\"><font style=\"font-size: 13pt\">30% class preparation and in-class participation</font></font></font></font></span></span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom:0cm\"><span style=\"background:transparent\"><span style=\"line-height:100%\"><font color=\"#000000\"><font face=\"Baskerville\"><font size=\"3\"><font style=\"font-size: 13pt\">30% short analysis of \u2018history in practice\u2019 texts</font></font></font></font></span></span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom:0cm\"><span style=\"background:transparent\"><span style=\"line-height:100%\"><font face=\"Baskerville\"><font size=\"3\"><font style=\"font-size: 13pt\"><font color=\"#000000\">40% final paper: </font><font color=\"#000000\">long-form</font><font color=\"#000000\"> analysis of the presentation of history in some non-academic historical thing (tv show, movie, novel, video/tabletop game, memoir, political debate, (group of) news article(s), exhibition, online museum, </font><font color=\"#000000\">Olympic spectacle</font><font color=\"#000000\"> etc etc).</font></font></font></font></span></span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom:0cm\"> </p> </div></div>",
