            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0cm\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span lang=\"EN-US\"><span style=\"color:black\">What was the Little Ice Age? In what ways did early modern Europeans experience the night? How did the Ottoman Empire handle epidemics? How did the whale shape the history of Tokugawa Japan? These are some of the questions we will address in the present course in environmental history. It studies how human societies and the natural environment made each other across different parts of the early modern (1500-1800) world. In course of the semester, we will learn about Europe, the Americas, Russia, China, Japan, South Africa, Egypt, and South Asia. We will cover themes as diverse as time, literature, colonialism, disease, animals, knowledge, frontier, resource, and climate. By the end of the course, students will have a considerable understanding of how the modern world came about through how early modern humans negotiated their environment.</span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0cm\"> </p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><ul><li><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\">Class Participation (25%)</span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\">Mid-Term Presentation (35%)</span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\">Term Paper (40%)</span></span></li></ul> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\"> </span></span></p><ul><li><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\">Class Participation (25%)</span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\">Mid-Term Presentation (35%)</span></span></li><li><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\">Term Paper (40%)</span></span></li></ul><p><span style=\"font-size:16px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\"> </span></span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0cm\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"color:#00000a\">Out of the 26 classes of this course, students are required to attend at least 20; they can be absent in up to 6 classes without having to explain themselves. They can be absent in more classes <i>only</i></span> <span style=\"color:#00000a\">for medical and/or other serious reasons.</span></span></span></p></div></div>",
