            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0in 0in 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">The course aims to analyze issues arising from interaction between environment and economy. The course is divided into four parts. First part delves into basic theory of externality, public goods. In the second part talks about valuation of environmental benefits and damages which then leads to examining policy instruments for pollution control. Lastly the course delves into issues associated with climate change and policies for their mitigation. </span></span></span></p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><ul><li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0in 0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">The students will be able to locate environmental issues in the broader theme of economics</span></span></span></li><li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0in 0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\">The students will be able to identify the environmental issues and identify and implement policies to minimize these issues</span></span></span></li><li style=\"margin:0in 0in 8pt 0.5in\"><font face=\"Calibri, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 14.6667px;\">The students will be able to understand the economics behind issues related to climate change and policies implemented</span></font></li></ul></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0in 0in 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Kolstad: Intermediate environmental Economics</span></span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0in 0in 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">A course in Environmental Economics: Phaneuf and Requate</span></span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0in 0in 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Policy Instruments for Environmental and Natural Resource Economics: Sterner and Coria</span></span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0in 0in 8pt\"> </p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>will share later</p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Class Participation is an important requirement</p></div></div><div><strong>Attachment</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><table><tbody><tr><td><a style=\"color:blue\" href=\"https://ams.ashoka.edu.in/UploadFiles/CourseCatalogueFiles/42c35039-d520-449d-a504-7c3f357a757e.docx\" download=\"Course Description.docx\">Course Description.docx</a></td></tr></tbody></table></div></div>",
