            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>We will be exploring the application of data science and statistics for analyzing sports data. You'll complete hands-on labs and projects to learn the methodology involved in tackling data science problems and apply your newly acquired skills and knowledge to real world data sets. You\u2019ll then segue into the field of sports analytics. Drawing from real data sets in baseball, basketball, hockey, soccer and cricket, you\u2019ll learn how to construct predictive models to anticipate team and player performance. You\u2019ll also replicate the success of Moneyball using real statistical models, using the Linear Probability Model (LPM) to anticipate categorical outcomes variables in sports contests and finally how to apply machine learning in a sports analytics context. (Thanks to Saravana Chilamakuri for proposing this course; much of the preceding text is from her course proposal.)</p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Ideally, ICP. No formal requirements, but the better a grounding you have in statistics and ML, the nicer the learning curve!</p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>50% course notes and paper reviews.</p><p>50% final paper.</p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>None. You snooze, you lose.</p></div></div>",
