            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin-bottom:0in; margin:0in 0in 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif\"><b>Course Description</b></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom:0in; margin:0in 0in 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif\">As Covid-19 has continued to ravage the world media has speculated if the pandemic means the end of globalization. With  all the restrictions on travel, will the interconnected and interdependent world retreat into a collection  of self-contained isolated communities.  The course will explore the phenomenon of  globalization and its connection with pandemics. We will take a historical perspective of the phenomenon -analyzing its different drivers and many barriers including succession of pandemics that have fallen in its path. We will take a special look at the impact of the pandemic on global power relations and the danger of fragmentation of the globalized world.</span></span></span></p><ol></ol><p> </p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin-bottom:0in; margin:0in 0in 8pt\"> </p><ol><li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0in 0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif\">The objective of this course is to examine the historical origins of pandemic and its intimate connection with the phenomenon of globalization. </span></span></span></li><li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0in 0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif\">We will explore the motivations that led different cohorts of humans to cross borders and over time create the interdependent globalized world of today. </span></span></span></li><li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0in 0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif\">We will examine the role of human migration, spread of faith , trade and  technology in this process. </span></span></span></li><li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0in 0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif\">We will analyze how the process of globalization has created both prosperity and hybridity as well as conflict and discontent. </span></span></span></li><li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0in 0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif\">With an eye on the past, we will study the reasons behind the latest phase of anti-globalization sentiment represented by populism embodied in Brexit and Trumpism</span></span></span></li><li style=\"margin:0in 0in 8pt 0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif\">We will analyze the rise and progress of the Covid-19 pandemic and its short-term and long-term  consequences.</span></span></span></li></ol></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0in 0in 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif\"><i>1.  Bound Together- How Traders, Preachers, Adventurers and Warriors Shaped Globalization</i>, Nayan Chanda</span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0in 0in 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif\">2.<i>What is globalization?</i>  Ulrich Beck</span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0in 0in 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif\">3. <i>The crisis of globalization: Democracy, Capitalism and Inequality in the Twenty-First Century</i> Edited by Patrick Diamond</span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0in 0in 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif\">4.  <i>Globalization Backlash</i> by Colin Crouch         </span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0in 0in 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif\">5. <i>Brexit: History, Reasoning and Perspectives</i> by David Ramiro Troiti\u00f1o, Tanel Kerikm\u00e4e, Archil Chochia</span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0in 0in 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif\">6. <i>Cultural Backlash: Trump, Brexit, and Authoritarian Populism</i> by  Pippa Norris, Ronald Inglehart</span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0in 0in 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif\">7. <i>Populism: A Very Short Introduction</i> by Cass Mudd</span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0in 0in 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif\">8. <i>Trump, Trade, and the End of Globalization</i> by David S. Jacoby</span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0in 0in 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif\">9. <i>The Coming Plague: Newly emerging diseases in a world out of balance</i> by Laurie Garrett</span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0in 0in 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif\">10. <i>The Age Of Pandemics 1817-1920: How They Shaped India And The World</i>  By Chinmay Tumbe</span></span></span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0in 0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif\">Class participation: 10%</span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0in 0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif\">Oral presentations: 15%</span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0in 0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif\">Book review: 20%</span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0in 0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif\">Quizzes: 5%</span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0in 0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif\">In-class response paper: 10%</span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0in 0in 8pt 0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif\">Final paper: 40%</span></span></span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>You are allowed three absences without excuse. More than three absences without excuse will incur grade cut. I reserve the right to fail you for multiple absences.</p></div></div>",
