            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"margin:0in 0in 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\" lang=\"EN-IN\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Research Methodology in Biology</span></span></span></b></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0in 0in 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\" lang=\"EN-IN\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">The course is to help you understand the process of scientific thinking and execution of scientific projects in an ethical way. The course structure has been designed for students who are starting their research in biology. It covers areas from understanding research publications to planning research projects and interpretation of your data.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0in 0in 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\" lang=\"EN-IN\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Faculty</span></span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\" lang=\"EN-IN\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">: Course Convenor  Dr. Subhashis Haldar. The course will be taught by a number of faculty from Biology Department </span></span></span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0in 0in 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><b><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\" lang=\"EN-IN\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Course structure</span></span></span></b></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0in 0in 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\" lang=\"EN-IN\"><span style=\"line-height:107%\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Scienti\ufb01c thinking and hypothesis framing: Introduction to the scienti\ufb01c method</span></span></span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\" lang=\"EN-IN\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Reading scientific papers </span></span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 8pt\"> </p><p style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\" lang=\"EN-IN\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Design of scientific studies, sampling, placebo, controls</span></span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 8pt\"> </p><p style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\" lang=\"EN-IN\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Lab and scientific project management</span></span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 8pt\"> </p><p style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\" lang=\"EN-IN\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Quality of data generation and errors in experimentation</span></span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 8pt\"> </p><p style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\" lang=\"EN-IN\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Interpretation of data, </span></span><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\" lang=\"EN-IN\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Correlation vs. causation, Signals and noise</span></span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\" lang=\"EN-IN\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Regulatory issues in modern biological research</span></span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 8pt\"> </p><p style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"> <span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\" lang=\"EN-IN\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Plagiarism, Scienti\ufb01c paper writing, ethics in publication</span></span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 8pt\"> </p><p style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 8pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\" lang=\"EN-IN\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\">Funding in science and grant writing</span></span></span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 8pt\"> </p><p style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 8pt\"> </p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>All the professors will grade independently. The final grade will be the average of alll these grades. </p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>75% attendence is mandatory. </p></div></div>",
