            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\">Taught by Achintya Prahlad</span></p><p> </p><p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">This course aims to expose students to the wide diversity of Indian music, with a strong practical component. The main focus will be learning how to sing, with knowledge of musical notes (swaras) and rhythm (taal). It will start at a fundamental level, and gradually become more advanced. The songs that are taught in the course will mainly be from regional musical forms in many languages of India, such as Hindi, Tamil, Kannada, Bangla, Marathi and Odia. Old film songs that are connected to these genres may also be included. The course will also help students integrate their musical skills into other courses in the performing arts department that they might take.</span></span></span></p><p style=\"margin:0cm 0cm 0.0001pt\"> </p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\">The majority of the course work will take place in class. Hence, attendance and participation in class are the main criteria for grading. </span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:Georgia,serif;\">Students can take up to 4 unexcused absences.</span></p></div></div>",
