            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>What kind of creature are you? A human being, no doubt. But what kind of creature is that? How should such a creature live? We will critically explore influential models of human nature in the Indic and Western philosophical traditions and their profound implications both for how we ought to live and our place in the social world. Readings include selections from the Upanishads, Vasist?h?a\u2019s Yoga, Plato, Aristotle, Hume, Freud, Mill, Railton, S\u00b4a\u00afntideva, Korsgaard, Foot, O\u2019Neill, Frye, Haidt, Milgram, Hobbes, Rawls, Bilgrami and others. </p></div></div>",
