            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>This course covers elementary probability theory, random variables and distributions, sampling distributions, point and interval estimation, and hypothesis testing. This course is waived off for students who have done two courses, Probability and Statistics (MAT 201) and Statistical Inference (MAT 311), taught by the Maths faculty. However, the two Maths courses should be taken before the students register for Econometrics in the Spring semester.</p><p>This course broadly covers the following topics: Random Variables: Descriptive Stats, Combinatorial Analysis, Probability, Random Variables. </p><p>Probability Distributions: Expectation and higher moments, Probability Distributions, Continuous random variables and distributions, Joint and Conditional Distributions including covariance and independence, Functions of a random variable. </p><p>Special Distributions : Bernoulli, Binomial, Poisson, Uniform, Normal and Exponential</p><p>Sampling Distributions and Hypothesis Testing: Sampling Distributions, Point estimators and their properties, Interval Estimation and Hypothesis testing</p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>This course is aimed at setting the foundation for statistical analysis. This sets the ground to learn about empirical techniques in the coming years. </p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>No prerequisites </p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>see the outline/ syllabus</p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Attendance is not mandatory </p></div></div><div><strong>Attachment</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><table><tbody><tr><td><a style=\"color:blue\" href=\"https://ams.ashoka.edu.in/UploadFiles/CourseCatalogueFiles/08e53d0c-b4ad-4015-81da-7c816e5ee808.pdf\" download=\"stats_priyanka_2021_detail.pdf\">stats_priyanka_2021_detail.pdf</a></td></tr></tbody></table></div></div>",
