            "html_details":"<div><strong>Office timing</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Wed 7-8pm</p><p>Fri 11-11:30 am<br> </p></div></div><div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Syllabus: Real and complex number systems. Limits of sequences. Monotonic sequences. Limits superior and limits inferior. Convergence of a series. Absolute and conditional convergence. Power series over real and complex numbers and their radius of convergence. Bolzano-Weirstrass Theorem, Cantor and Heine-Borel Theorems. Point-wise and uniform continuity. Sequences and series of functions. Pointwise and uniform convergence of sequence of functions. Integrals and derivatives of sequences and series of functions. Elementary transcendental functions. Improper integrals, Riemann-Stieiltjes integral. Idea of Lebesgue integral, Weierstrass approximation Theorem.</p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>To become familair with the basic objects and techniques of analysis.</p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Our main textbook will be Principles of Mathematical Analysis, 3rd edition, by Walter Rudin</p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>The purpose of this course is to get thigs into your head and into your comfort zone. For that you will need to study, review, stay up to date with the course etc etc... all those things that students are supposed to do. To help this process, we will have two types of evaluation. One will be small simple quizzes in class. These will not be announced. For these you will obviously need to be present in the class. If you have mysterisouly joined the class just at the moent of the quiz that quiz isn't going to count. I'll do these often, and they will be short. At the end I will drop the lowest 2 or 3 scores. The total weight of this will be 25% of your grade.</p><p>We will have three longer quizzes spread out through the semester. I'll announce dates well in advance. The total weight of this will be 50% of your grade.</p><p>25% of your grade will come from HW's.</p><p>Here is how letter grades will be assigned:</p><p>90 and up: A</p><p>80 and up: B</p><p>70 and up: C</p><p>50 and up: D</p><p>Below 50: F</p><p>Pluses and minuses as well as borderline cases will be at my discretion.</p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>I expect you to attend all classes. However I understand that there will be times when you are unable to attend, for whatever reason. At such times you do not need to inform me. However if you are going to be absent for a number of sessions, please do let me know.</p></div></div>",
