            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>With so much white noise in the millennial digital space, opinion, social media posts, and content writing are often confused with journalism. <br><br>This course is a primer on how to identify, report, and write authentic news reports. The course will include an introduction to journalism fundamentals and ethics, the concept of news- what is noteworthy and why, techniques to find news stories, building news sources, and practising various news writing formats. <br><br>Through lectures and readings, it will teach how to practice clear, accurate, informative, reporting and the art of listening, observing, interviewing and note-taking to dig out stories from strangers and unfamiliar territories. It will teach research skills to find and evaluate sources, put the information in a context, and check facts in a journalistic fashion to structure a professional-quality news report. <br><br>Writing formats like the ground report, feature, profile, analysis, investigative, narrative, graphic non-fiction, will also be touched upon. Lectures on editing and copyediting will teach students how to give a final shape to a news piece like it is done in an actual newsroom. <br><br>Reading lists and a collective weekly news bulletin will be used to identify news peg and what fits into the current news cycle. Through editorial discussions in a manner conducted in newsrooms, writing practice, and best examples of national and international reports, the student will know how to write a first-hand news report in an impactful, concise, and contextual manner.  </p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><br>Reading one newspaper-hard copy or e-copy is mandatory. </p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>There will be three major assignments along with weekly bulletins and in-class assignments. </p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Only two absences permitted in the 13 week course</p></div></div>",
