            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Instructor: Prof. Mukesh Sud, (Visiting from IIM Ahmedabad) Course Description</p><p>The course examines how an entrepreneurial mindset enables identifying and exploiting opportunities and pursuing a life style of your choice. We will also discuss how entrepreneurs deal with uncertainty and learn from failure.</p><p>The classes will be delivered using case studies and experiential learning through peer discussions.</p><p>Some of the Key Topics include : -</p><p>Recognizing opportunities \u2013 How does an entrepreneurial mind identify problems, recognize opportunities and scan the market to assess the prospects of the entrepreneurial venture.</p><p>Effectual Entrepreneurial Thinking \u2013 Effectuation is a concept of entrepreneurial thinking which has been a popular thought globally, specially in the last 2-3 years. Students will identify the key effectual traits that an entrepreneur needs to cultivate.</p><p>Language of Entrepreneurs \u2013 The world of entrepreneurship comes with its own set of jargons, standards and fundamentals. This section will familiarize a new comer with the world of an entrepreneur\u2019s dialect.</p><p>Entrepreneurial Networking \u2013 Today, Social networks are an important component in everyone\u2019s lives. How does an entrepreneur leverage their social network and how can entrepreneurial resources be drawn effective networking.</p><p>Corporate Entrepreneurship \u2013 Entrepreneurship can also be practiced within large organizations, by being a driver of innovation. So how does one manage to be entrepreneurial while working in large corporates? What are the other forms of entrepreneurship that can be practiced?</p><p>What are the key ingredients that drive success in entrepreneurial firms? How do</p><p>entrepreneurs capitalize on new ideas and bring them to market? How is an</p><p>entrepreneurial mindset different from a managerial one?</p><p>About the Faculty</p><p>Prof. Mukesh Sud<br>(Visiting Faculty from IIM Ahmedabad)</p><p>Mukesh Sud is an Associate Professor of Business Policy and Entrepreneurship at</p><p>IIM Ahmedabad.</p><p>Previously Dr. Sud has taught entreprenreurship at a Liberal Arts University in the</p><p>US. Prior to entering academia he was an entrepreneur in Bangalore and ran</p><p>technology companies in the field of Thermal Sprayed Coatings.</p><p>Dr Sud received his PhD from the Indian Institute of Management, Bangalore and an</p><p>engineering degree from the Indian Institute of Technology (IIT Delhi). His deatiled</p><p>profile is avaiable at the IIMA Website.</p></div></div><div><strong>Attachment</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><table><tbody><tr><td><a style=\"color:blue\" href=\"https://ams.ashoka.edu.in/UploadFiles/Content/ProgramCourseInfo/ENT-1003[ENT-1003-1]/ddab1047-d4f8-4b8b-9ed6-a0218a088db2.pdf\" download=\"Mindset Syllabus  Monsoon Sem.pdf\">Mindset Syllabus  Monsoon Sem.pdf</a></td></tr></tbody></table></div></div>",
