            "html_details":"<div><strong>Office timing</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>This is an online semester. You can send me an email and fix an appointment.</p></div></div><div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Linear Algebra has been important in itself and for study of other subjects: advanced calculus, functional analysis, geometry, statistics, physics and engineering. In recent years it has seen new applications in numerical analysis, coputation, image processing, machine learning,....</p><p>A knowledge of linear algebra and matrix analysis beyond the fist course is crucial for many subjects. This course is designed for that purpose.<br> </p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>The following book covers material roughly at the level of this course</p><p>S. R. Garcia and R. A. Horn,  A Second Course in Linear Algebra. </p><p>You may also look into books by</p><p>S. Axler,</p><p>M. E. Taylor</p><p>Friedberg,Insel and Spence</p><p> </p><p>You should choose only one of them that you like. Use it for supplementary reading in addition to what is done in class.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p><br> </p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Two assignments 20</p><p>Two midterm tests 40</p><p>Final exam  40</p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Regular attendance is encouraged. For success in this course it is essential to do homework exercises regularly and right from the beginning.<br> </p></div></div>",
