            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>What is the relevance of reading postcolonial literature in contemporary classrooms? Do we still define ourselves through the category of the colonial and/or postcoloniality? Is it redundant to do so?  This course begins with such questions but moves beyond, to read certain postcolonial literary texts as not only physically rooted in material spaces \u2013 often poor, backward and non-modern spaces \u2013 but also examine how they embody the spirit of such locations, often untranslatable and un-exportable. </p></div></div>",
