            "html_details":"<div><strong>Office timing</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>By appointment - see the course syllabus for instructor contact details and protocol.</p></div></div><div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>This course will provide a foundation in statistics for economists. The topics to be covered include elements of probability theory, random variable, distribution functions, transformation of random variables, law of large numbers, central limit theorem, statistical estimation, con dence interval and hypothesis testing. </p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>This course serves as a pre-requisite for future courses in Econometrics.</p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Required textbook for the course is as follows:</p><p>DeGroot, M., and M. Schervish, Probability and Statistics, Fourth Edition, (Pearson Education) - Indian edition is available.</p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Assignments 30%<br>Midterm Exam 35%<br>Final Exam 35%</p><p>Absolute grading applies for this course. The correspondence between the numerical and letter grade is according to the \"Policy Documents\" in the university's website.</p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>None. See the course syllabus for policies regarding use of electronic devices during in-person classes, plagiarism etc.</p></div></div><div><strong>Attachment</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><table><tbody><tr><td><a style=\"color:blue\" href=\"https://ams.ashoka.edu.in/UploadFiles/Content/ProgramCourseInfo/ECO-5400[ECO-5400-1]/1196818d-e823-46b0-a6f9-ff9bf51c42dc.pdf\" download=\"Course_Syllabus_Statistics.pdf\">Course_Syllabus_Statistics.pdf</a></td></tr></tbody></table></div></div>",
