            "html_details":"<div><strong>Office timing</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">To fix an appointment for office hours, please send an email to sanjukta.datta@ashoka.edu.in </span></p></div></div><div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">Welcome to the world of broken pots, buried shipwrecks and stolen idols. Conceptualized as an introductory course on the study of material remains, it is divided into two broad sections. The first explores fine-tuned methods employed by archaeologists to analyze available data in the reconstruction of the past; major theoretical turns in the history of the discipline; the relationship between history and archaeology; and heritage management. The second section engages with scholarly but accessible accounts of archaeological cultures from two different parts of the world. While the first half of the course will be a combination of lectures and class discussions, the remaining half will be completely discussed based. </span></p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">1. Familiarity with the basic principles of archaeology</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">2. Ability to navigate technical information and draw broad inferences based on that for historical reconstruction </span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">3. Appreciation for accessible presentation of archaeological material</span></p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">The syllabus along with a short bibliography will be emailed to enrolled students on the first day of class.  </span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">The grading rubric will be outlined in the syllabus.</span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">The course has a strict attendance policy, allowing for a total of <strong>five (5) </strong>absences during the semester.</span></p></div></div>",
