            "html_details":"<div><strong>Office timing</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>TBA</p></div></div><div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>This course takes students to the next level of macroeconomics after the introduction they would have<br>obtained in the Principles course of the first year. The focus is on the three equation model (IS-Monetary<br>Rule-Phillips Curve) and how that plays out in a closed and in an open economy. The analysis of business<br>cycles is introduced.</p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>This course is a notch above the introductory macro course. Broadly we will cover the following topics under four heads. One, The 3-equation model (IS-Monetary Rule-Phillips Curve) in the closed economy. Second, 3-equation model in the open economy. Third, Introduction to Real Business Cycles and if time permits we will also touch upon the fourth topic of  Introduction to Intertemporal Macroecomics. </p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>1. Carlin, W., &amp; Soskice, D. W. (2014). Macroeconomics: Institutions, instability, and the financial system. Oxford University Press, USA</p><p>2. Olivier Blanchard : Macroeconomics. Pearson. Seventh (Global) Edition.</p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Grading will be done on the basis of three exams. One will be a mid-term exam with a weightage of 20 percent plus another mid-term with a weightage of 20 percent and there will be an end-term/final exam with a weightage of 60 percent. </p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>No mandatory attendence. </p></div></div><div><strong>Attachment</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><table><tbody><tr><td><a style=\"color:blue\" href=\"https://ams.ashoka.edu.in/UploadFiles/CourseCatalogueFiles/6ca62adb-b6b1-4ca4-97a2-d9bd9a6de5fa.pdf\" download=\"macro1_priyanka_2021_detail.pdf\">macro1_priyanka_2021_detail.pdf</a></td></tr></tbody></table></div></div>",
