            "semester":"Monsoon 2021",
            "document":"",
            "html_details":"<div><strong>Office timing</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">To fix up an appointment for office hours, please send an email to sanjukta.datta@ashoka.edu.in</span></p></div></div><div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">Who is a Hindu and what defines Hinduism? In the absence of a historical founder and a single text outlining the tenets of the religion, what unites the bewildering variety of precepts and practices within the broad umbrella of Hinduism? Does the long, dynamic history of Hinduism corroborate its popular characterization as an eternal, tolerant and non-proselytizing religion? As the subtitle suggests, the course will examine such widespread stereotypes about Hinduism from a historical perspective. In this exciting journey, we will encounter foundational texts, sacred centres of worship, mystical devotional cults, militant ascetic orders and social reform movements. Glimpses of some of the finest pieces of pre-modern Indian religious literature, such as  hymns of the <em>Rig Veda</em> and devotional poetry of medieval<em> bhakti </em>saints, will be an added attraction. </span></p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">1. Familiarity with the historical evolution of Hinduism. </span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">2. Ability to critically engage with individual components constitute Hindu beliefs and practices.</span></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"> </p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">The syllabus along with a short bibliography will be e-mailed to enrolled students on the first day of class.</span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">The details will be provided in the syllabus.</span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">The course has a strict attendance policy, allowing for a total of <strong>five </strong>(5) absences throughout the semester.</span></p></div></div>",
