            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>WAR AND MEDIA</p><p>Rather than detail the various ways in which warfare has been represented in media accounts, this course is concerned with studying the content of media technologies/interfaces that are built into weapon systems. Typically the course will study drone warfare, night vision glasses, internet-enabled rifles and camera lenses as they come to further the conduct of what is considered to be \u2018hyper-real\u2019 warfare. The perspective is to explore the coordinates of a scopic regime and its relationship to targets of opportunity. The course will show how the scopic regime is central to an understanding of the security state. A second part of the course will focus on the kinds of collectives that are engendered in the interface between war and media. Ranging from a literature that deals with the body of the soldier, to the significance of considering targets of opportunities as populations, rather than as people, the course will analyze the force of contemporary forms of bio-politics.</p><p>This is a 300 level course and a basic familiarity with current readings on collective violence will be a bonus. There will be a mid-semester and end term examination in the form of a take home test. Each student will be expected to make a seminar presentation.</p><p>The readings for the course will be made available before the start of the second class. Needless to add, it is essential that students come well prepared for the class.</p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Students will gain a familiarity with emerging trends in contemporary scholarship on war, surveillance and security.As mentioned above</p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>To be distributed before the second class.</p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>As mentioned above</p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>We will follow university guidelines on attendance</p></div></div>",
