            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Course: Leadership Lessons from the Road Less Travelled</p><p>Faculty: Prof. Rashmi Bansal</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Course Description</p><p>The primary mode of learning will be the story telling method. High achieving entrepreneurs will speak about their life stories, how and why they started out, what were/are their motivators, what difficulties and challenges they faced along the way, how they built their team, how they managed to work with very little capital and so on. The course aims to enable the participants to appreciate the various facets of leadership and the behavior and traits of successful leaders through listening to the life stories of a dozen high achieving entrepreneurs and interacting with them.</p><p> </p><p>About the faculty</p><p>Rashmi Bansal is an Indian non-fiction writer, entrepreneur, and a youth expert. She is the author of ten books on entrepreneurship, the most famous being Stay Hungry Stay Foolish, which narrates the journey of twenty-five successful entrepreneurs. As reported by the New York Times, collectively her books have sold over a million copies and have been translated into numerous languages. After attending St Joseph's High School in Colaba, she studied at Sophia College for Women before earning an MBA in 1993 from the Indian Institute of Management Ahmedabad.</p><p> </p></div></div>",
