            "html_details":"<div><strong>Office timing</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Tuesday &amp; Thursday 10:10 - 11:40 am</p></div></div><div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Basic Inorganic Chemistry: Periodic Properties, General Chemistry of Main Group, Transition, and Inner Transition elements</p><p>This course provides an overview of fundamental topics in inorganic chemistry</p><p>Details: SI Units,  Atomic structure,  Pauli Principle, Slater and Hunt Rules, Aufbau Principle, Energy levels of atoms, The periodic properties of elements: The radius of atom and ion, Ionization Energy, Electron Affinity, Electronegativity, Molecule Structure, The introduction of bonding theory (Ionic and Covalent Bonding), Valence Bond Theory, Ionic Bond and Metalic Bond; Crystal Structure, Lattice Energy</p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Atomic structure</p><p>Explain the electronic structure of the atom<br>Categorize the atomic structure<br>Relate the quantum numbers and atomic orbitals</p><p>Periodic table of elements</p><p>Relate periodic properties of elements<br>Express the periodic properties of elements</p><p>Estimate molecular structure</p><p>Relate the molecular structure and Lewis dot notation<br>Calculate formal charge<br>Demonstrate the resonance forms of molecules<br>Explain the molecular geometry with VSEPR theory<br>Calculate binding energy</p><p>Types of chemical bonding</p><p>Define the chemical bonds<br>Adapt Valance Bond theory to molecule structure<br>Explain the covalent bond with hybridization</p><p>Truly you will get an essence of Inorganic Chemistry and how it's related to our everyday life.</p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Basic Inorganic Chemistry F.Cotton, G. Wilkinson, P. Gaus</p><p>Inorganic Chemistry: Principles of structures and Reactivity J. Huhey, E. Keiter, R. Keiter</p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Class Quiz (from Practice questions)   30 Marks (best of all exam)</p><p>Midterm assignment                             30 Marks</p><p>Final exam or assignment                    40 Marks</p><p>Total                                                     100 Marks</p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Minimum 60% attendance</p></div></div>",
