            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>All stories are migrants.  Looking at how stories have migrated across cultures over history, we will think about how any reading of a story is always a reading from a specific point in space and time that creatively reimagines that story in a new language and cultural context.  Focusing on how stories from Ovid\u2019s Metamorphoses and the Silk Road masterpiece A Thousand and One Nights were reimagined by Shakespeare, and then how Shakespeare\u2019s retellings have been reimagined all over the world from the UK and the US to Sudan, Sierra Leone and India as poems, films, plays, novels, and graphic novels, this course will ask students to reimagine themselves too, as creative readers.  The final project will be a group reimagining of one of the stories in the course in a medium and language of your choice \u2013 Urdu dastangoi, Hinglish play, English film, multilingual multimedia installation, or anything else.</p></div></div>",
