            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>This course is required of, and limited to, MA and MLS students writing their theses in English.It is an introduction to the art of writing a long research paper in critical and creative form, and will feature a different speaker each week discussing a precirculated article.Students will read and discuss these from the point of view of the architecture of an argument: questions of structure, form, audience, archive, stakes, and style will be paramount.They will also write abstracts, an annotated bibliography, and a prospectus for their final thesis project.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p></div></div>",
