            "html_details":"<div><strong>Office timing</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Friday from 2.50 pm to 6.20 pm</p><p>AC 03 Lab 105 (Chemistry)</p></div></div><div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>In this practical course, we will provide you a comprehensive hands-on experience in Chemistry. The course covers all aspects of chemistry including physical, inorganic, and organic. We will walk you through some lab works which you can directly correlate to your daily life. You will experience the powerful nature of chemistry to architect at the atomic level and apply chemistry knowledge to qualitative and quantitative analysis of food/drinks/cosmetics, and even medicines. Eventually, we will train you to develop chemistry expertise for biological applications like bioconjugation and medicinal chemistry.</p><p>These are the 9 laboratory practicals listed below you have to do a minimum of 6 to get full credit for this course.</p><p> </p><p>1. CMC and aggregation numbers by fluorimetry/UVVis/conductometry<br>2. Spectrophotometric Determination of the pKa of Bromothymol Blue</p><p>3. Determination of fluoride ion concentration in toothpaste<br>4. Determination of iron content in a supplement tablet</p><p>5.  Isolation of \u03b2-carotene from carrot/tomato and their characterization using UV-spectroscopy<br>6.  Isolation of limonene from its natural source and physicochemical analysis.<br>7. Click chemistry reaction: Purification and characterization of organic compounds<br>8. Azo compound synthesis and their purification and characterization</p><p>9. TBD</p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Students will get a basic understanding and hands-on chemistry across disciplines. The course will eventually develop into an advanced-level course, especially in bio-organic/inorganic and medicinal chemistry.</p><p>Students will learn separation-based techniques such as column chromatography and thin-layer chromatography (TLC).</p><p>Students will develop skills in quantitative, spectroscopic, and spectrometric analysis.</p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>A lab notebook will be provided to each student before the lab course.</p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Class                          35</p><p>Practical notebook     35</p><p>Test                            30</p><p>Total marks                100</p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>80% attendance.</p></div></div>",
