            "html_details":"<div><strong>Office timing</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>A mutually convenient time and venue will be decided. To schedule additional office hours, email me at anup.padmanabhan@ashoka.edu.in</p><p> </p></div></div><div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>For More details please refer to the course document here - <strong>https://docs.google.com/document/d/1LyEl3NqN3T2bGtczZ_voUQ4cVZQh_ukIyacaMpO1Qa4/edit?usp=sharing</strong></p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Course Objectives     : Cells are the fundamental unit of life. It carries out all (well\u2026 almost all!) the physiological processes essential for its survival and propagation. Within the cell, each of these processes is accomplished by molecular-machines. What are these processes and how do these mini machines carry out the cellular functions? How do these cellular machines know the right place and the right time to carry out appropriate functions?</p><p>In this introductory Cell Biology course, we will start by exploring some of the essential processes at the cellular level and understand how the relevant molecular machines manage to carry out these processes with such amazing fidelity and efficiency. The primary focus of this course will be on eukaryotic cells, but as and when needed we will draw comparisons with prokaryotic cellular processes to appreciate their similarities and distinctness.</p><p>By the end of this course, the participant is expected to have a good conceptual grasp on basic cellular mechanisms, the molecular machinery involved, and their functional regulation within a cell.</p><p> </p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Primary Textbook</p><p>Molecular Biology of the Cell , Alberts B, et. al ( If you dont have access to physical copy, you may access the contents here - https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK21054/)</p><p>Supplementary Materials</p><p>Molelcular Cell Biology - Lodhish et. al  ( If you dont have access to physical copy, you may access the contents here - https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK21475/)</p><p>https://www.ibiology.org/ ( Wonderful resourcce of lectures for students who wish to understand basics as well for those who wish to know advancced concepts)</p><p>Primary Literature - will be shared as references in lecture slides. </p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Grading details is detailed here - <strong>https://docs.google.com/document/d/1LyEl3NqN3T2bGtczZ_voUQ4cVZQh_ukIyacaMpO1Qa4/edit?usp=sharing</strong></p><p> </p><p><strong>IMPORTANT - This course is intended towards developing an independent line of thinking and reasoning towards understanding cell biology concepts. Academic Integrity happens to be the most important ingredient in achieving that. Any student guilty of , aiding or abetting any form of Academic Dishonesty will score a \u2018zero\u2019 in the relevant assessment. Repeat offences will attract a \u2018Fail\u2019 grade. All steps in this regard will be taken in strict adherence to the Ashoka Academic Integrity Policy. </strong></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Attending lectures would be helpful in Quizzes, but attendance is not Mandatory. </p></div></div>",
