            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Taught by Hiten Noonwal</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\"> </span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">This course aims to decipher links between fashion and fiction. Students will explore varied forms of performing arts, theatre, music videos and cinema as a medium to understand iconology, aesthetics and image creation. Students will learn to analyse, visualise and interpret the literal text / storyline and to envision the textile / costume / clothing appropriately suited for the context. There will also be an emphasis on the importance of visual psychology in the context of communication through narrative. This subject will help students to understand the importance of props and other physical factors like space, lighting etc.</span></p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Grading for all co-curricular courses is based on attendance and class participation.</span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Unexcused absences will affect the student's grade.</span></p></div></div>",
