            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Taught by Ankit Pandey</span></p><p> </p><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">The course aims to introduce lighting as a tool in the process of theatre making and storytelling. It focuses on what light is, what it can do and how it is perceived in today\u2019s world. It explores light\u2019s innate ability and responsibility to change or support the meaning of a narrative, both for the audience and the performer. We will learn how to interact with different lighting sources and understand their characteristics in order to create meaningful visual compositions. Moreover, the course aims to elucidate how lighting enables you to guide the eye of the audience to what and how things need to be seen and perceived. The goal is to approach the process of designing lights for any performance across genres by understanding how to interpret text, action, and narrative into design choices and create suitable visual imagery.</span></p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Grading for all co-curricular courses is based on attendance and class participation.</span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Unexcused absences will affect the student's grade.</span></p></div></div>",
