            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Taught by Pramod Emjay</span></p><p> </p><p> </p><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">The last hundred years have fundamentally changed storytelling, as the art of creation has moved beyond the constraints of literature and the static visual. With the multitude of tools, techniques and forms evolved, we are equipped as never before to tell stories both old and new. This course will be an elementary exploration of how other worlds come into being, with a focus on SciFi, Horror and Fantasy worldbuilding. We will look at the visual storytelling, storyboarding, soundscapes, cinematic techniques, character creation, rulesetting and tropes that helped develop epics &amp; immortalise classics. The course will span film, graphic novels, literature, and other media while students apply these lessons through periodic hands-on workshops and learn to breathe life into their creations.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\"> </span></p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Grading for all co-curricular courses is based on attendance and class participation.</span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Unexcused absences will affect the student's grade.</span></p></div></div>",
