            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Taught by Himanshu Bablani</span></p><p> </p><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">This course will introduce students to the world of Interactive Art and Design. It will help them explore the possibilities of combining Art and Design with Electronics and Digital Fabrication.  They will engage with Interactive and Kinetic Art Installations, smart products, Robots, 3D printers etc. Through group work, the students will learn the basics of Digital Computer Aided Design. They will practice the process of Rapid Prototyping to convert their designs to physical prototypes. They will also be introduced to Arduino and Electronics Prototyping. The students will then learn about Digital Fabrication techniques like 3D Printing, Laser Cutting and Engraving. They will finally combine all these processes to make a working prototype of interactive and kinetic art.</span></p><p> </p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Grading for all co-curricular courses is based on attendance and class participation.</span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Unexcused absences will affect the student's grade.</span></p></div></div>",
