            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Taught by Neel Chaudhuri</span></p><p> </p><p> </p><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">This course divides itself into two concurrent streams: one, a workshop on writing for performance and two, explorations in the staging of text. We will be exploring the multiple traditions and roots of dramatic writing and performance in the Indian context - from narrative poetry and oral storytelling to the more modern modes of structured writing and digital media. The course will encourage you to find your unique approach to writing for performance while considering aspects such as structure, character, dialogue, rhythm and purpose. Simultaneously, we will explore multiple modes of \u2018staging\u2019 performance that traverse the live and the recorded, the physical and the digital, the audio and the visual. Participants will work collaboratively to realise the texts they are writing in performance, experimenting with form and medium. The final output could be anything from a reel to a radio play. </span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\"> </span></p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Grading for all co-curricular courses is based on attendance and class participation.</span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Unexcused absences will affect the student's grade.</span></p></div></div>",
