            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Taught by Shinto Mathew</span></p><p> </p><p> </p><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Kalaripayattu is a movement practice which is both an embodiment of physical culture as well as a martial art.  Associated with Kerala, its origins can be traced as far back as at least the 12th century.  In a traditional worldview, becoming a warrior implies a training process that involves the focussing of mind, body and spirit in equal measure. The slow and steady preparation needed to grasp a martial art is emphasised in this course.  Both the fundamental philosophy and the physical foundations of Kalaripayattu will be explained and explored through practical execution.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\"> </span></p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Grading for all co-curricular courses is based on attendance and class participation.</span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Unexcused absences will affect the student's grade.</span></p></div></div>",
