            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Taught by Arman Ali Dehlvi</span></p><p> </p><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\"> This is a Dhrupad vocal music course specialising in the Sufiyana compositions of the Dagarvani tradition of Dhrupad. In this course, students will learn to sing traditional Sufiyana Dhrupads that have been passed down through the generations in the Dagar family. They will learn how to improvise in the Alaap and composition sections of the Raag while also learning how to sing with the Pakhavaj drum by learning it's basic Taals or rhythm cycles. This course will briefly cover the history of the Dagarvani tradition along with basic Dhrupad music theory. There may also be field trips to major Sufi centres in and around Delhi to get a sense of Sufi music and culture.</span></p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Grading for all co-curricular courses is based on attendance and class participation.</span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Unexcused absences will affect the student's grade.</span></p></div></div>",
