            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Taught by Ranjana Dave</span></p><p> </p><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">If you\u2019ve always wanted to learn an Indian dance form but are wondering how to get started, this course is for you! The \u2018sculpturesque\u2019 positions that we see in Indian dances are made up of tiny details - all put together with rhythm, flow, and synchronicity. This course will focus on conditioning techniques that help us build the strength, grace and coordination required.  Students will be guided to work towards understanding their bodies and their movement patterns, and to identify the specific skill sets they need to grow as dancers. The classes will draw from diverse sources, including yoga, kalarippayattu, and traditional conditioning exercises that draw on commonly used movements and positions from Indian dances. They will also address specific aspects of dance training - such as working with hand gestures, eye movements and rhythmic patterns. No prior training or experience is required to join.</span></p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Grading for all co-curricular courses is based on attendance and class participation.</span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Unexcused absences will affect the student's grade. </span></p></div></div>",
