            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Taught by Ainee Farooqui &amp; Nusrat Ansari</span></p><p> </p><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">The word Dastangoi refers to the art of storytelling. Dastans were epics, often oral in nature, which were recited or read aloud and in essence were like medieval romances everywhere. Dastangoi died out with its last traditional proponent Mir Baqar Ali in 1928. Over the last 15 years it has seen a major revival thanks to the scholarship of the late S. R. Faruqi and the efforts of his nephew Mahmood Farooqui, who has trained dozens in this modern art form. We will analyse and compare traditional and modern Dastangoi performances using practical examples and lecture demonstrations. We will also simultaneously work on performative aspects of dastangoi- voice modulation, poetry recitation, pronunciation, expression. Towards the end, the students will be required to stage one of the traditional dastans.</span></p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Grading for all co-curricular courses is based on attendance and class participation.</span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Unexcused absences will affect the student's grades.</span></p></div></div>",
