            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Taught by Phuntsog Dolma</span></p><p> </p><p> </p><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">The Tibetan language and Buddhism have played a crucial role in the history of Tibet. The language is not only spoken and used by Tibetans, but also used in many other countries in Asia like Nepal, Mongolia, Bhutan, parts of China and places around the trans-Himalayan regions of India. The study of the Tibetan language gives one access to Tibetan history, religion and culture which is highly influenced by Buddhism. This course is designed to introduce students to Tibetan alphabets and basics of Tibetan grammar, and to provide context for the socio-cultural and political history of Tibet and its bordering neighbours.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\"> </span></p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Grading for all co-curricular courses is based on attendance and class participation.</span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Unexcused absences will affect the student's grade.</span></p></div></div>",
