            "html_details":"<div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Taught by Achintya Prahlad</span></p><p> </p><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">This course is about the richness of the German language. Beginning with basic pronunciation and grammar, it will be focussed on learning conversational German, through talking to each other, and also through watching films, news and so on. While the course will largely consist of standard German, there will be a discussion of dialects of German in Germany and other countries such as Switzerland and Austria. The course will also include poetry old and new \u2013 including Goethe\u2019s works \u2013 and literature such as Grimm\u2019s fairy tales and Franz Kafka\u2019s stories. Culture and traditions, such as the traditions surrounding Christmas and Easter, will also be talked about.</span></p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Grading for all co-curricular courses is based on attendance and class participation.</span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Unexcused absences will affect the student's grade.</span></p></div></div>",
