            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Taught by Gautam Choubey</span></p><p> </p><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">The emergent technologies of mass communication have a significant bearing on the newfound visibility of Bhojpuri. Thanks to the cassette revolution of the late 80s, single-screen theatres, and, of late, a YouTube-steered resurgence of the vernacular, Bhojpuri appears stronger than ever. Yet, beyond the stereotypes, little is known about the culture. This course proposes to introduce the fascinating world of Bhojpuri through an assortment of cultural specimens\u2014literary, folk, cinemati and ethnomusicological. Inter alia, it seeks to engage with Bhojpuri\u2019s history, its relationship with other dominant languages, a popular-yet-divisive movement for its official recognition, and the questions of visibility and obscenity that have long plagued its prospects.</span></p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Grading for all co-curricular courses is based on attendance and class participation. </span></p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">Unexcused absences will affect the student's grade. </span></p></div></div>",
