            "html_details":"<div><strong>Office timing</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Wednesday 11:50 - 12:50 (By prior appointment)</p></div></div><div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Are you tired of staring at a screen? Have you ever looked out of the window, looked at a bird and wondered what it is? Then this is the course for you! This course is oriented towards beginners who want to learn about India's wildlife and the rationale behind wildlife conservation. This course will cover the basics of  species identification, animal behaviour and species-based conservation decision making. It will also introduce students to India's eminent researchers and conservationists, who will interact with students through guest lectures.</p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Learning skills to observe nature and distinguish species</p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Students will be graded on class participation, quizzes and the term paper.</p> </div></div>",
