            "html_details":"<div><strong>Office timing</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Tues     11:50 \u2013 13:20</p><p>Thurs   11:50 \u2013 13:20</p></div></div><div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Conservation requires out-of-the-box thinking and out-of-the-library learning! It involves engaging with a diverse set of stakeholders, balancing multiple demands and constraints, and taking tough decisions under conditions of limited information and high uncertainty.</p><p>In this course, you will interact with conservationists who are working in real-world conservation landscapes. You will hear from a diverse set of people involved in conservation, ranging from scientists, to youth leaders, to practitioners, to local community conservation leaders. Through their stories, you will learn of challenges, opportunities and experiences we may face while practicing conservation science or action.</p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>The goal of this course is to make you recognise the complexity of conservation, and appreciate the diverse approaches people use to achieve real-world conservation impacts.</p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Group Project 1           \u2013 40%</p><p>Group Project 2           \u2013 40%</p><p>Participation               \u2013 20%</p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Students are expected to attend all classes.</p></div></div>",
