            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>This course will introduce students to major themes and issues pertaining to Muslim politics both at the international level and in Indian domestic politics. By the end of the semester, students will be able to understand the various ways Islam is mobilized in the political sphere and how Muslims engage with politics as Muslims. Students will be invited to debate and question core concepts such as Islamism and its translation in the practice of politics. The course will also cover a wide-range of case-studies from South Asia and West Asia\u2014such as the Israel-Palestine conflict, the Iranian Revolution, the issue of blasphemy, or the question of Muslim Personal Law.</p></div></div>",
