            "html_details":"<div><strong>Office timing</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>By appointment.</p></div></div><div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Gravity is different, unlike other fundamental forces its description is not based on \u201ccharges\u201d and \u201cfields.\u201d The best description of gravity is provided by the Gen- eral Theory of Relativity which is a theory of spacetime geometry. This theory not only provides a stunningly successful description of all known gravitational phenomenons, but is also a theory of immense beauty and sophistication. The main aim of this course is to introduce the fundamental concepts of General Theory of Relativity, a further aim is to apply it to modern cosmology.</p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Student will learn the fundamental concepts of General Theory of Relativity and will use it to describe black holes and the big-bang model of the universe.</p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><h2>Text Book</h2><p>The course will closely follow Gravity: An Introduction to Einstein\u2019s General Relativity by James B. Hartle</p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>The student will be graded on take home problem sets. The university polices on plagiarism will be strictly followed while grading the problem sets.</p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Attendance is required.</p></div></div><div><strong>Attachment</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><table><tbody><tr><td><a style=\"color:blue\" href=\"https://ams.ashoka.edu.in/UploadFiles/Content/ProgramCourseInfo/PHY-4810[PHY-4810-1]/91d8376d-8a82-4696-9790-9cff4bb96e1e.pdf\" download=\"GR-2021-CourseOutline.pdf\">GR-2021-CourseOutline.pdf</a></td></tr></tbody></table></div></div>",
