            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>This is a first course in Probability and Statistics.  Elements of probability theory such as a probability space, random variables, distributions and various examples of these will be presented.  The Statistics component will involve its principles, elementary parametric statistics such as estimation and regression will be done.  A more detailed syllabus will be given in the first class.</p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Understand principles of probability theory and begin to think like a statistician.</p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p> <span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Statistical Inference</span>, George Casella and Roger L. Berger,Second Edition, Duxbury Thomson Learning (UK).</p><p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">A first course in Probability</span> , Sheldon Ross</p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Will be announced in class</p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>None</p></div></div>",
