            "html_details":"<div><strong>Office timing</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Thursdays 2 to 3 pm IST. Please email for alternate slots. </p></div></div><div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Welcome everyone to the course \"Curating Global Film Culture\".</p><p>This course looks closely at the global evolution of New Waves from the 1960s and their unique artistic language. The course will be looking at key movements to appreciate, not only the relationship of cinema and society, but also the development of core theories and intellectual debates that such waves have raised. This course examines the language of cinema at a global level, and it also introduces students to the practice of historical investigation with the use of archives (in a broader sense) and tailored archive-based festivals, and related curatorial practices.</p><p> </p><p>This course will enable students to develop practical skills that will allow for a gradual progress into professional practices; the course will push students beyond the boundaries of mnemonic and systematic learning of global art and mainstream cinema. Moreover, through a hands-on approach the students will learn how to build a coherent rationale for film based events such as exhibitions, film retrospectives and creative projects that use archives as their main source of inspiration.     </p><p>Best,</p><p>Monia</p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>see attached list </p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p> the course has one assignment which consist of a portfolio of 1500 words, based on a film history exhibition that students will have to curate. That will form the full 100% of the module mark. Internally it will be split into 50% for the contribution to the exhibition and 50% for the written portfolio). Students will be given formative assignments and classwork through the course </p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Absences are not encouraged. Students will be penalized for over 2 unexcused absences. </p></div></div><div><strong>Attachment</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><table><tbody><tr><td><a style=\"color:blue\" href=\"https://ams.ashoka.edu.in/UploadFiles/Content/ProgramCourseInfo/MS-3459[MS-3459-1]/53bf231b-c4e8-4863-8c2a-849e11e5da3d.pdf\" download=\"CURATING GLOBAL FILM CULTURES_BLACKBOARD.pdf\">CURATING GLOBAL FILM CULTURES_BLACKBOARD.pdf</a></td></tr></tbody></table></div></div>",
