            "html_details":"<div><strong>Office timing</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Class Timing: 11:50 am - 1.20 pm Tue &amp; Thu</p></div></div><div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Introduction to Communication Research Methods provides an overview of the concepts, methods, and tools by which communication research is designed, conducted, interpreted, and critically evaluated. This course will help you become a knowledgeable consumer of communication research as you develop skills in gathering, organizing, interpreting and presenting research information in a competent and ethical manner.</p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>(1) master the concepts and technical vocabulary of communication research, and be able to use this language appropriately</p><p>(2) comprehend the relationship between theory and research methods in the study of communication as a social science</p><p>(3) assess the ethical choices of researchers in conducting and presenting research</p><p>4) compare and contrast four major research methods (experimental, survey, textual analysis, and naturalistic inquiry) used to investigate communication behavior</p><p>(5) develop skills necessary for conducting communication research</p><p>(6) develop the ability to clearly communicate, both orally and in writing, the findings of original communication research to a lay audience</p><p>(7) become an intelligent consumer of research\u2014able to read, understand, explain and critically evaluate communication and other research reported in scholarly journals as well as in the popular press.</p><p> </p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Will be shared in syllabus.</p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Will be shared in syllabus.</p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Ashoka Policy</p></div></div>",
