            "document":"https://ams.ashoka.edu.in/UploadFiles/Content/ProgramCourseInfo/IR-2029[IR-2029-1]/b9dacf46-9673-4e81-bee9-a4b377180efd.pdf",
            "html_details":"<div><strong>Office timing</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Classes will begin at 2:50 PM and end at 4:20 PM  on Tuesdays and Thursdays.</p></div></div><div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>As Covid-19 has continued to ravage the world media has speculated if the pandemic means the end of globalization. With  all the restrictions on travel, will the interconnected and interdependent world retreat into a collection  of self-contained isolated communities.  The course will explore the phenomenon of  globalization and its connection with pandemics. We will take a historical perspective of the phenomenon -analyzing its different drivers and many barriers including succession of pandemics that have fallen in its path. We will take a special look at the impact of the pandemic on global power relations and the danger of fragmentation of the globalized world.</p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>The objective of this course is to examine the historical origins of pandemic and its intimate connection with the phenomenon of globalization.<br>We will explore the motivations that led different cohorts of humans to cross borders and over time create the interdependent globalized world of today.<br>We will examine the role of human migration, spread of faith , trade and  technology in this process.<br>We will analyze how the process of globalization has created both prosperity and hybridity as well as conflict and discontent.<br>With an eye on the past, we will study the reasons behind the latest phase of anti-globalization sentiment represented by populism embodied in Brexit and Trumpism<br>We will analyze the rise and progress of the Covid-19 pandemic and its short-term and long-term  consequences.</p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Required Reading Before the Course (Either 1, or 2 and 4 and 9)</p><p>1. Bound Together- How Traders, Preachers, Adventurers and Warriors Shaped Globalization, Nayan Chanda</p><p>2.What is globalization?  Ulrich Beck</p><p>3. The crisis of globalization: Democracy, Capitalism and Inequality in the Twenty-First Century Edited by Patrick Diamond</p><p>4.  Globalization Backlash by Colin Crouch        </p><p>5. Brexit: History, Reasoning and Perspectives by David Ramiro Troiti\u00f1o, Tanel Kerikm\u00e4e, Archil Chochia</p><p>6. Cultural Backlash: Trump, Brexit, and Authoritarian Populism by  Pippa Norris, Ronald Inglehart</p><p>7. Populism: A Very Short Introduction by Cass Mudd</p><p>8. Trump, Trade, and the End of Globalization by David S. Jacoby</p><p>9. The Coming Plague: Newly emerging diseases in a world out of balance by Laurie Garrett</p><p>10. The Age Of Pandemics 1817-1920: How They Shaped India And The World  By Chinmay Tumbe</p><p> </p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p> Students will form two or three person teams to make oral presentations on assigned themes. (15%)<br>Students will submit a 4-page (1500 words) book review. Book title will be announced at the beginning of the semester. (20%)<br>Five quizzes to be taken in the class (5%)<br>Two written papers.   </p><p>a. Short paper - 2 pages to be written during class as personal response to the theme discussed.  (20%)<br>b. Final paper \u2013 5-7 pages  to be submitted at the end of  the semester. (40%)</p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Class attendance is mandatory.  Students should notify me during the first week of the semester of their intention to be absent from class for special occasions.</p><p> If you miss more than three classes I reserve the right to deduct grades or fail you.</p><p>  During online class please keep your video on.</p></div></div><div><strong>Attachment</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><table><tbody><tr><td><a style=\"color:blue\" href=\"https://ams.ashoka.edu.in/UploadFiles/Content/ProgramCourseInfo/IR-2029[IR-2029-1]/b9dacf46-9673-4e81-bee9-a4b377180efd.pdf\" download=\"IR 2029 class schedule.pdf\">IR 2029 class schedule.pdf</a></td></tr></tbody></table></div></div>",
