            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>In this course we will look at texts across genres \u2013 novels, short stories, essays, poetry, films \u2013 and ask the following questions: What do these texts tell us about caste? How do they erase caste while telling us something else? If caste isn\u2019t explicitly mentioned, what are the tools we may use to understand the caste action at play? Is caste a religious issue? If it is, is it particular only to Hinduism? Can we read for caste only through the lens of identity? We will encounter texts that are immediately identifiable as dealing with issues concerning caste, and those that \u2013 with some prodding \u2013 show us the many insidious ways in which caste configures our lives. We will think about our own experiences with caste to inform our opinions of the texts we read, and learn to articulate them as cogent arguments across various writing exercises.</p></div></div>",
