            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>This course introduces students to the fundamentals of film history, film analysis and film theory. The students will learn about different periods and movements in film history such as Early Cinema, German Expressionism, Soviet montage cinema, French Impressionism, Classical Hollywood, Italian neorealist cinema and the Iranian New Wave. The students will also learn about major theoretical approaches to the study of film with an emphasis on classical film theory debates. We will examine basic concepts of film form and study the methods of film analysis. Texts will include theoretical writings by Walter Benjamin, Siegfried Kracauer, Sergei Eisenstein, Andre Bazin, David Bordwell, Laura Mulvey, Gilles Deleuze and Tom Gunning. We will also be analyzing films by directors such as D.W.Griffith, Alice Guy-Blach\u00e9, Germaine Dulac, Robert Weine, Sergei Eisenstein, John Ford, Vittorio De Sica, Ritwik Ghatak, Yasujiro Ozu, Agn\u00e9s Varda, Jean-Luc Godard and Abbas Kiarostami.</p></div></div>",
