            "html_details":"<div><strong>Office timing</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Monsoon 2021: 02/09/21 - 16/12/21<br>Class Timings: 4.30-7.30 pm Thursday<br>Instructor: Dr. Sanna Balsari-Palsule<br>Email: sanna.palsule@ashoka.edu.in</p></div></div><div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>This module introduces key topics in the science of personality and individual differences. This<br>course will shift away from traditional trait-based perspectives of human personality to<br>contemporary scientific research on the science of personality change. The course will cover<br>topics such growing empirical research on the variability of personality across contexts, roles and<br>situations, and its impact on important life outcomes, from work, relationships to overall well-<br>being. The course will cover the science of extraversion, self-monitoring and authenticity, the dark<br>side of personality and attraction and compatibility. The course will additionally explore the new<br>neuroscience of personality that explains individual differences in human behaviour.</p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>- Introduce contemporary scientific perspectives, empirical findings and debates from<br>personality science<br>- Critically engage with new perspectives on personality change and explore how they apply<br>to important life domains, from culture, the workplace, relationships to the self.</p></div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Grading is divided between two written assignments and one presentation.</p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>TBD</p></div></div>",
