            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><address>*<span style=\"font-family:georgia,serif;\">The course will be taught by an instructor from Taiwan Education Center.</span></address><p>Introduction to Mandarin language is a beginner\u2019s course, specifically designed for students with no exposure to Modern Standard Chinese (Putonghu\u00e0 ???). The course will introduce students to the Chinese language and culture and focus on basic speaking, listening, reading, and writing skills. This includes an introduction to phonetics, basic vocabulary, and expressions of daily use. The course will prepare the students to attain a certain level of understanding and proficiency in Chinese language through interpretive, interpersonal, and presentational modes. It will integrate Chinese culture into language learning through both written and audio-visual means to familiarize students with the culture and language.</p><p>This course is the first part of a two-semester sequence. Students signing up for the Level I introductory course will mandatorily have to continue with Level II in the next semester. At the end of the two semesters, students will be able to read and comprehend Chinese texts on various topics moderately without the aid of pinyin and tone marks. In the second semester they will be expected to give presentations in Chinese on a prepared topic and write short paragraphs and compositions on a limited range of topics and situations. The course will require a commitment of 4 hours every week \u2013 in 4 sessions of an hour each.</p><p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">(Please note that this course will not count towards a Concentration or Minor in International Relations or the History-IR Major.)</span></h4></div></div>",
