            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><br>Welcome to \u201cAuditory &amp; Temporal Cognition\u201d! This course will: take you on a journey deep into the human central auditory system, its structure and functions, ranging from simple pitch discrimination to rhythm perception, and all the way up to language and music processing, the two most sophisticated \u201cend uses\u201d of auditory cognition. We will also cover about the related dysfunctions, including developmental and neurological ones, with one specific focus on rhythm and timing in the human brain as the basis for music, language - and even movement.  <br>We will start with the inner ear and move on into the brain, along the ascending auditory pathway, discover specialisation of the relevant brain structures, learn about the role of expertise (e.g. musicianship) and go full circle by touching on predictions and top-down projections. <br>Each of the lectures will in the following session be complemented by presentations and critical discussion of related articles of your choice, which will range from relevant classical studies to hot-of-the-press ones.<br> </p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>-</p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>TBD, but a combination of presentations, exams and assignments will be administered</p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>TBD</p></div></div>",
