            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Things are us. Things are the material stuff that we can touch, smell and feel. Things can show and recall a point of view. They can figure as non-tactile hyper-objects, such as the internet, or move us as embodied signs and symbols. Things turn amazingly into thinking tools shaped and reshaped by social context and perspective. Things are storied, thought-laden, and plentiful. And so we have to cherry-pick things that have been unravelled for us by a venerable, anthropological canon ( the sacred totem; money). And delve into contemporary thing theories about new things (mobile phones; visual images), the thingness of discarded objects (waste; hair), and touch on the production and seduction of things in our times. People do and think such extraordinary thinks with things!</p></div></div>",
