            "html_details":"<div><strong>Overview</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Office Timings: </p><p>By appointment</p><p>Tuesday, Thursday \u201310.00 \u2013 11.00 AM,<br>Wednesday 2.30 \u2013 3.30 PM</p><p> </p><p>Bombay cinema, affectionately called \u201cBollywood\u201d has become the background music to our lives, whether as innocent entertainment or \u2018time pass\u2019. However we often overlook Bollywood\u2019s serious intent and its strong ideological underpinnings. Right from its inception, with Dadasaheb Phalke\u2019s Raja Harishchandra (1913), it has shaped the public narrative in India.</p><p>While the themes of Hindi films have changed over the years --from the patriotic \u2018Mother India\u2019 to the sports-feminist \u2018Dangal\u2019, the presentation of nationalism, sports and sexualities may just be old wine in new bottles. We will examine these ideologies primarily through the lens of gender.</p><p>We will also explore how the language, fashion, music, dance, and social values embedded in Bollywood films are disseminated. International theoretical readings from ideas of nationalism, film, gender, class, and cultural studies, and literature from various parts of the world will underpin our discussions of Bombay\u2019s film industry and our exploration of the values and ideologies embedded in apparently innocent entertainment.</p><p>[Please note \u2013Supplementary readings and films may be assigned during the course of the semester. Film viewing is mandatory. Even if you have seen the film before it is important to see it again for this class and with a view to the topics and ideas being discussed. Please find a way to view the films on your own. Ashoka may not be able to arrange screenings.]</p></div></div><div><strong>Learning Outcomes</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>One of the course\u2019s goals is to recognize these themes and develop the analytical tools to effectively \u201cread\u201d a text/film, empowering us to identify challenge mainstream norms.</p></div></div><div><strong>Requirements (Reading List and other materials)</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p><strong>List of Films under consideration</strong>   [all films will be viewed outside of class time]</p><p>Broad themes</p><p><strong>Nationalism</strong></p><p>Mother India (1957)</p><p>Purab aur Paschim (1970)</p><p>Border (1997)</p><p><strong>Sexual Preferences</strong></p><p>DDLJ (1995)</p><p>Aligarh (2016)</p><p>Ek Ladki Ko Dekha Toh Aisa Laga (2019)</p><p><strong>Sports</strong></p><p>Lagaan (2001)</p><p>Dangal (2017)</p><p>Saand ki Aankh [Bullseye] (2019)</p><p><strong>Miscellaneous to be considered -</strong></p><p>3 Idiots (2009)</p><p>Lipstick under my Burkha (2017)</p> </div></div><div><strong>Grading Rubric</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Class participation + attendance \u2013 5%</p><p>Oral Class Presentations- (To be discussed.) 10% - 5 minutes each.</p><p>Written Assignments- 85%</p><p> A total of 3 short papers and 1 long final paper.</p><p><strong>Paper 1 </strong>due \u2013 Saturday September 25, 2021 @ 11.30PM = 15% (750-800 words)</p><p>on any aspect of nationalism and national cinema as seen in Bollywood.</p><p><strong>Paper 2</strong> due \u2013Saturday October 23, 2021 @11.30 PM = 15% (800-850 words)</p><p>on any aspect of sexualities as seen in Bollywood.</p><p><strong>Paper 3 </strong>due \u2013Saturday November 20, 2021 @ 11.30 PM = 20% (850-900 words)</p><p>on any aspect of Sports or Education as seen in Bollywood.</p><p><strong>FINAL PAPER</strong> due\u2013Saturday December 4, 2021 @11.30PM = 35% (1000-1500) words.</p> </div></div><div><strong>Attendance Policy</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><p>Attendance is mandatory and will impact your final grade. You may miss 3 classes during the semester without penalty.  After three absences, a letter from your final grade will be deducted for each missed class. If you have 3 unexcused absences, I will reserve the right to fail you for the course.  Coming more than 5 minutes late to class will count as an absence.</p></div></div><div><strong>Attachment</strong><div class=\"cmsDescp\"><table><tbody><tr><td><a style=\"color:blue\" href=\"https://ams.ashoka.edu.in/UploadFiles/CourseCatalogueFiles/5adb5c5f-ede3-42c2-a724-24469786aafe.docx\" download=\"Syllabus- Bollywood and Gender.docx\">Syllabus- Bollywood and Gender.docx</a></td></tr></tbody></table></div></div>",
